title: yummy caramel bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup of milk over low heat until caramels are melted; set aside.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine butter, dry cake mix, 1/3 cup milk and nuts. Stir by hand until dough holds together.

title: six week's bran muffins
directions: Blend oil, eggs and buttermilk. Add cereal. Let stand until cereal softens. Sift all dry ingredients. Add to other mixture. Grease muffin tins (small tins make better muffins). Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes. May refrigerate for up to 6 weeks.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Place potatoes in bottom of casserole.
Cover with meat.
Mix together sauce, milk, soup and spices.
Pour over meat and potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted (5 to 10 minutes).

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Do not stir anything until all ingredients are in bowl, then beat.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Chop up onions and peppers; add in frying pan with ground beef.
Let brown; drain.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer.
Pour into casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top, then lay sliced cheese on top of biscuits.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, salad dressing and Hidden Valley dip mix and pour on crust.
Chop any vegetables you prefer and place on top of mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese or taco sauce on if you like.

title: pigtails
directions: Mix oleo, baking powder, anise flavoring, sugar and eggs. Beat until oleo is dissolved.
Add flour, mixing dough with hands.
If dough is too soft, add more flour so that dough is not sticky.
Form a log and cut in pieces about 3 inches wide.
Roll into a pencil thin rope.
Twist rope to form cookie.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for about 10 - 12 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn out onto a wire cooling rack.
Frost with Pistachio Frosting.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix eggs, milk, flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and the salt in medium bowl (batter will be slightly lumpy).
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in 12-inch ovenproof skillet until bubbly; pour batter into skillet.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 20 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake until crisp and golden, 10 to 15 minutes (do not open oven door during baking).
Transfer pancake to serving plate.

title: baked creamed cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage
and
place
in greased baking dish.
Mix sugar, salt,
flour
and
pepper;	blend
in cream.
Pour over cabbage and top
with bacon slices.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°. Remove lid to crisp bacon before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Microwave sour cream and cream cheese for 45 seconds; stir.
If lumpy, microwave 10 to 15 seconds more.
Then mix taco seasoning mix in with sour cream and cream cheese.
Mix red pepper seasoning in with previous ingredients.
Spread mixture in pan or glass dish. Spread on thick.
Layer pan in this order on top of dip:
lettuce, green onions, green peppers, tomatoes and grated cheese.
Serve with a big bag of tortilla chips.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add peanuts to the melted chocolate and stir. Spoon out by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand at room temperature.

title: meat balls on picks
directions: Beat egg and water.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in shallow pan for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Serve on cocktail picks.
Makes 60 to 70.

title: dutch-oven cobbler
directions: Line Dutch oven with foil.
Pour fruit on the bottom. Sprinkle cake mix on top of fruit.
Pour 7-Up on top of cake mix. Cover and cook over charcoals for approximately 1 hour.
While cooking, place 6 to 8 briquets
on the lid to cook the top.
Dab with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: cheese 'n chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pastry pie shell for 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat eggs; blend in cream, dressing, chicken, cheese and pimiento.
Pour into prepared shell.
Bake for 40 minutes or until pie tests done. Makes 6 servings.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Put
all ingredients in quart jar and shake.
Pour into popsicle
molds
or
paper cups with inserted popsicle sticks. Freeze.
Tear off paper cups and eat.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat yolks until light on medium speed.
Add sugar, then boiling water.
Lower speed; add dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour in jelly roll pan lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Roll in damp cloth while hot.
Unroll, add jelly and roll up again.

title: pork chops in mushroom soup
directions: Brown pork chops in a skillet.
Put in a slow cooker and cover with mushroom soup.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: creamy rotini salad
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and milk.
Add cheeses and butter to egg mixture.
(Stop here if you mix ahead of time, the night before, etc.)
When ready to bake, fold in the baking powder and flour.
Add sausage (can also add crumbled bacon if desired). Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch or larger Pyrex pan.
Bake 40 minutes, uncovered, at 375°.

title: corned beef with cabbage
directions: Wash brine from corned beef using 3 to 4 waters.
Cover with cold water.
Add garlic and peppercorns; simmer until meat is tender (1 1/2 hours for young beef or up to 5 hours for older beef).
Add carrots and onions for last hour of cooking.
Add cabbage the last 20 minutes.
Serve corned beef on platter with vegetables around it.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eloise's best squash dressing(low-fat)
directions: Make a skillet of cornbread using skim milk, Egg Beaters and 1 onion.
This can be made the day before.
Crumble cornbread and hamburger buns.
Mix together.
Add Mrs. Dash and black pepper. Mash the cooked squash in cornbread mix.
Add chicken broth. Cook in Teflon skillet until consistency wanted or bake in oven at 350°.

title: franks and cheese snack
directions: Place American cheese and miniature frankfurters on crackers. Toast in toaster oven or broiler until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Saute onions and celery until crisp-tender.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and rosemary.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add wild rice and chicken.
Heat through.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix sour cream and soda and set aside.
Cream shortening, butter and sugar together and add eggs.
Blend in sour cream mixture; add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, depending on thickness of dough.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook on low heat for a couple of hours.
Add tomato sauce and paste last.
Add a pinch of cinnamon and cook until thick.
Add a beef bouillon cube.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese and taco seasoning.
(A food processor works well.)
Layer mixture, lettuce, onion, black olives and Cheddar cheese.
Cover with salsa and Cheddar cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tutti-frutti lemon
directions: In large bowl, combine undrained pineapple, undrained mandarin oranges and undrained fruit cocktail with flaked coconut and lemon juice.
Sprinkle lemon pudding mix over fruits and lightly combine.
Just before serving, add bananas and top with whipped topping.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes. Cool on pan, then remove.

title: meat loaf
directions: Dice up onion; wet crackers and squeeze out water.
Beat eggs. Mix this with ground beef (with hands).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Drain fat and spread ketchup over top.
Drain fat as it accumulates.
Baking time:
about 45 to 60 minutes, according to your oven.

title: moist chewy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan sprayed with Pam and over very low heat, melt chips and butter.
Stir occasionally until well blended; remove from heat.
Add baking mix, sweetened condensed milk and egg; stir well.
Stir in nuts.
Spray Pam on bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour brownie mixture into dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes; cool slightly.
Cut into squares.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: Cook pinto beans in water until juice is a little thick (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Do not add oil or anything to pinto beans while cooking.
Brown ground turkey or hamburger.
Rinse with hot water.
Drain, then add pinto beans.
Add green beans (drained), green pepper, banana peppers, tomatoes, salt and pepper.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine cheeses and set aside to use as filling.
Saute chopped onions or steam until tender in microwave.
Add cream of chicken soup, sour cream and green chilies.
Heat almost to boiling.
Put 2 or 3 tablespoons of cheese mixture in tortilla. Cover with 2 or 3 tablespoons of soup mixture, then roll and arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Top enchiladas with remaining soup mixture, then top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop
tomatoes	first
in
enamelware pan and pour salt over. Let
stand	while chopping	onions	and
peppers.
When everything is
chopped, pour briny water off tomatoes and add all ingredients
together and simmer slowly until peppers and tomatoes are
tender
and change color.
Do not overcook.
Do not boil. Makes 14 pints.
Very good with fish.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix dry angel food cake mix, lemon pie filling and coconut. Bake in 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift together flour and salt, set aside.

Combine together next four ingredients and 1/2 c. of flour mixture.	In a mixing bowl, cream together butter, sugar and eggs; adding one at a time. Add soda and buttermilk, mix well.	Then add flour and fruit mixture alternating until it is blended.
Pour batter into a 10 inch tube pan; bake at 300° for two hours or more.

title: new potatoes by mary
directions: Scrub the potatoes and peel a strip of skin from around the center of each potato, about 1/2-inch wide.
Place the potatoes in a pan and add boiling water to a depth of 2-inches.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; boil gently for 20 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.
Drain.
Return to the heat for several minutes to dry out.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix melted butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour and continue beating.
Add coconut and pecans. Pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Top with pecans dipped in melted caramels.
Place pecans on top of chewy cake.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: If you want to make a chicken pie, double the dumpling recipe and make a topping for the chicken and dumplings.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs. Add salt and pepper (optional).
Dunk bread in egg mixture, both sides, then into crushed corn flake mixture.
Fry in pan with a little margarine or butter until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mash up together and form ball.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Pour batter into an 8-inch greased pan.
Press blueberries into top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zesty salsa supreme
directions: In small bowl, combine cucumbers, pepper, carrot, taco sauce, green chillies and parsley until well blended.
Spoon a rounded teaspoonful mixture onto each Triscuits; top with a dollop of guacamole.

title: egg salad
directions: Slice eggs in half.
Smash egg yolks until smooth and spreadable.
Add remaining ingredients.
Re-fill egg whites.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together. Fill greased muffin cups half full. Do not let rise. Bake at 375 degrees until brown. Makes 12.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large baking pan.
Mix water and soup well. Add to pan.
Sprinkle rice over all.
Salt and pepper chicken and lay on rice.
(Use salt lightly.) Sprinkle bouillon crystals on top of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 400°. Take foil off and brown chicken, about 15 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites and gradually add gelatin, beat until dissolved.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to boil to firm ball stage.
Add to egg whites.
Beat until loses gloss.
Add cherries and nuts.
Drop by spoonful.

title: ham and swiss rolls
directions: Slice dinner rolls in half.
Flip open and set aside.
In a bowl mix melted butter, poppy seeds, and minced onion.
Brush mixture on inside of bread.
Layer with ham and cheese.
Put top of bread back on and layer with butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Slice along slots.

title: virginia pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavorings; alternate flour and milk, beating after each addition.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Cool partially in the pan. Glaze with confectioners sugar and orange juice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat well the milk, cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add vanilla, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix until fluffy.
Pour into already made pie crust.
Refrigerate 8 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and pour into crust.
Chill until serving time.
Can sprinkle nuts on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and crumble ground beef. Drain off fat. Add taco seasoning with just a little water (2 tablespoons). Cook and stir for a few minutes. Cool. Toss all salad ingredients together. Just before serving, add broken up chips and hamburger mixture. Use full bottle of dressing.

title: strawberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, including juice.
To help fruit thaw, cut through the blocks.
Add pineapple and juice.
Work quickly before mixture begins to set. Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a 13 x 7 x 2-inch flat container. Spread sour cream on top.
Add remainder of gelatin mixture as a third layer.
Refrigerate for gelatin to set.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Coat chicken with Bisquick.
Fry in oil until brown.
Put in pot with water to cover.
Add onion, celery and carrots.
Cook 45 minutes.
Add chicken soup.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: In large saucepot, heat oil.
Add flour and cook over low heat, stirring often, until roux turns dark brown and develops a nut-like aroma.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic and cook until vegetables are tender.
Slowly add chicken broth, a little at a time, stirring after each addition; bring to a boil.
In separate skillet, brown chicken pieces until golden in color and add to pot with tomatoes, bay leaf and pepper sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and okra; cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, salt and pepper well; shape into bite size balls.
Place balls into a shallow baking dish.
Mix and heat
chili
sauce,
grape	jelly
and
lemon juice until melted. Pour heated mixture over meat balls.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour, then uncovered for 30 minutes.
Good and easy appetizer.

title: fruit batter pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk together. Pour batter into large pie dish.
Add fruit with 3/4 cup sugar per pint of fruit.
Add cinnamon to apples or nutmeg to peaches.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Top with vanilla ice cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray baking dish with Pam or other vegetable oil spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can bake 1/2 and freeze the other 1/2 for later use.
Freezes very well in Ziploc bag.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 1 hour or more.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Bake in tube or loaf pan.
Frost as desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook the frozen green beans as directed on package.
Place the cooked green beans in a baking dish.
Mix the 2 cans of mushroom soup (uncooked) with the beans.
Place the onion rings on top of the green bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic - corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vegetable cooking spray.
Pour into baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cabbage oriental
directions: Saute cabbage, celery, pepper and onion in oil over low heat 10 minutes.
Add soy sauce and paprika.
Stir and serve.

title: bunch punch
directions: Bring 4 cups sugar and 3 cups water to a boil for 5 minutes and allow to cool completely. Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight or freeze about 16 hours so it will be icy.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together, Bake at 350 for 35 minutes.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt margarine; combine soup, rice and almonds or mushrooms; stir and put in deep dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer if rice needs more time.

title: irene's gingerbread
directions: Cream together oil and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs. Sift flour, then sift again with spices added.
Mix baking soda with 2 teaspoons water
and add to oil/sugar mixture.
Add molasses, then add the flour and spices.
Lastly, mix in the hot water.
Pour mixture in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300°
for about 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add sugar, egg and dates.
Stir all ingredients over low burner until thick. Take off burner and add the vanilla, pecans and Rice Krispies.
Stir together.
Take some coconut and spoon the ingredients in it. Roll in balls.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions; drain well.
Mix with other ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top and return to oven for an extra 5 minutes.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium-low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Pour over popcorn, mixing well. With buttered hands, form into balls.
Makes 12 medium balls.

title: elf bites
directions: Heat sugar and karo syrup to boiling.
Stir in peanut butter, then Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper; cool.

title: laney's cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate 24 hours.
Roll in chopped nuts and serve.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in blender or process until smooth.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1-gallon freezer. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen for 1 hour.

title: mahatma corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine hamburger, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Fill manicotti shells with 1/4 of filling and place in baking dish. Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with remainder of filling. May include Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Double this recipe for a 9 x 13 pan and bake a little longer.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Boil sugar and water 2 minutes.
Cool and add fruit.
Line cupcake pans with paper liners.
Pat mixture into cupcake liners and freeze.
After freezing you can place fruit cups into storage containers and store in freezer until ready to eat.
Good for dessert or snack.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift three times with baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add milk with soda, then eggs and flour.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine. Chill.
Freeze mold of water and serve with punch.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a small bowl, combine oil and morsels.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes until morsels melt.
Stir in peanut butter. Pour over cereal.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and peanuts into a 2-quart microwave measuring cup.
Do not cover.
Cook on High for 5 minutes. Stir.
Cook on High for 13 to 15 minutes, until hard crack stage (300° on the candy thermometer).
Check temperature several times during the last few minutes.
Do not leave thermometer in microwave.
Stir in butter, soda and vanilla until light and bubbly.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Spread. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: hamburger cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat or sausage.
Drain and set aside.
Melt cheese and add Ro-Tel.
Mix well.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and can of mushrooms.
Add meat.
Mix well.
Serve warm.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift all ingredients into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Make 3 holes in the mixture.
Drop in one hole 1 teaspoon vanilla, into the next hole put 1 teaspoon vinegar and in the last hole put 5 tablespoons melted shortening.
Pour 1 cup of water over all.
Mix well.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bean dip
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot until hot, stirring occasionally.
Serve with chips.
Double for more than 12 people.

title: banana bread
directions: Add the eggs to the bananas.
Beat well.
Add the shortening to the sugar.
Mix.
Mix all the dry ingredients with the nuts. Add the dry ingredients to the wet all at once and beat only until dampened.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan on bottom only.
In medium mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, cloves, zucchini, milk, eggs and nuts.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until blended, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: bob's potato salad
directions: Chop very fine the first 4 ingredients; layer in Pyrex dish. Mix cottage cheese and Miracle Whip together; spread over this. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and bacon bits over the top.

title: mexican rice
directions: Rinse rice; drain.
In 2-quart boiler, add rice and all ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce to low heat.
Cover and cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and fluff.
Serve with additional picante sauce if desired.

title: polish sausage and green peppers
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until brown.
Add additional ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter fudge pie
directions: Spread 1 cup Cool Whip on bottom of pie crust.
Freeze 10 minutes.
Carefully spread fudge sauce over topping.
Stir milk into peanut butter in a large bowl until smooth.
Add pudding mix. Beat with a wire whisk for 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in remaining topping.
Carefully spoon over fudge sauce.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand 15 minutes or until pie can be cut easily.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Serves 8.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press into baking pan.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Parboil onions for 10 minutes, drain.
Mix soup, onions, milk and crackers.
Put in casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: oatmeal
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; add chopped apples and raisins and cook 1 minute.
Add oatmeal and cinnamon.
Reduce heat; cover. Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle each dish with 1/2 teaspoon sugar each when serving.

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally until tender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Unroll crescent rolls into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread crumbled sausage on top of crescent rolls. Spread frozen hash browns over sausage layer. Mix eggs and milk together. Then pour evenly over the hash brown layer. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: ham scalloped spuds
directions: Toss sliced spuds, chopped onions and diced ham in large bowl, mixing well.
Combine flour and seasoning; mix well and toss with spud mixture until evenly distributed.
Spread in large, greased flat pan (9 x 13-inch or 12 x 17-inch).
Pour milk over spuds; cover pan with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until spuds are almost fork-tender.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese. Allow to sit 5 minutes to melt cheese; serve.
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Strain oysters, reserving 1/4 cup liquor.
Combine crumbs, butter and salt.
Spread 1/3 of crumbs in an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round casserole dish coated with vegetable spray.
Cover with half the oysters; sprinkle with pepper.
Repeat layers.
Combine cream, oyster liquor and Worcestershire sauce and pour over oysters.
Top with lots of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Cut into squares.

title: dipper's nuggets chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Heat 3-inches vegetable oil in large heavy saucepan over medium-high heat until oil reaches 375°; adjust heat to maintain temperature.
Meanwhile, beat egg and water in large bowl until well mixed.
Add flour, sesame seed and salt, stirring to form smooth batter.
Dip chicken pieces into batter, draining off excess.
Fry chicken, a few pieces at a time, in hot oil about 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Enjoy.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: grandma's chicken 'n dressin'
directions: After broiling chicken, strain off the broth.
Mix the broth, the 2 cans of soup and the diced onion in a large broiler.
Bring this mixture to a broil.
Then reduce heat and simmer until onions are fully cooked.
Pour this mixture over the crumbled cornbread and mix.
Then add poultry seasoning.
After seasoning to your taste, debone the chicken and add the chicken chunks to the mixture.
Bake in large pan for 30 minutes or until top of dressing is lightly browned.
Bake at 350°.
This is great and what makes it an even more special dish is that my grandmother taught me how to cook it.
Believe me, she is a great cook!

title: no bake butterscotch bars
directions: Put graham cracker crumbs, miniature marshmallows, coconut and walnuts in big bowl.
Beat eggs, sugar and margarine together. Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir often as it burns easily. Melt butterscotch chips and add the peanut butter.
Pour cooked ingredients over first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with last 2 mixtures for frosting.
Keep in refrigerator.
Also can be frozen.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Melt chocolate and shortening in large saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies start to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not overbake. Cool slightly.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes about 32 cookies.

title: cheesy oven fries
directions: Wash potatoes well and cut each into 8 wedges; set aside. Combine cheese, salt, garlic powder and paprika.
Stir well.
Dip potato wedges in melted margarine.
Arrange in a single layer in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and browned.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: banana trifle
directions: Prepare pudding mixes as directed on package using 2 cups milk. Stir in cinnamon and nutmeg.
Slice bananas; fold into pudding with sour cream.
Before pudding sets, pour into trifle bowl or 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass pan.
Line immediately with ladyfingers.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 9 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and pudding well. Stir in half and half and vanilla. Add whole milk to top of paddle in freezer.
Makes 1 gallon!

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Cook in large Dutch pot or in large container to put in the oven.
Add onion and tomatoes to steak; cook on medium heat for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
While cooking, sprinkle with parsley.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: green vegetable casserole
directions: Cook limas and broccoli according to package directions.
Do not salt.
Drain.
Mix sour cream, water chestnuts and soups. Combine vegetables and soup mixture.
Spread in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt oleo and mix with cereal.
Spread on top of vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and Crisco.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix 3 cups of oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in tight container. Shake jar before using.
Use about 2 teaspoons of mix per cup of very hot water.

title: cantonese spareribs
directions: Parboil ribs about 30 minutes.
Combine all ingredients for sauce.
Marinate ribs in sauce at least 2 hours.
Bake in 350° oven or barbecue.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine vegetable oil and sugar.
Add eggs, apples and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix and add nuts. Bake in a greased and floured oblong glass pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: graham cracker cookie bars
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Mix the next 3 ingredients and add to the heated mixture.

title: communion bread(for the lord's supper)
directions: Stir into a ball and knead.
Roll very thin on a floured surface.
Bake, ungreased, approximately 20 minutes at 275°.
May take less time, depending on oven.
Don't let get too done and brittle.

title: angel food dessert - so quick
directions: You will need 1 large bowl.

title: chocolate-toffee bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil; spray with Pam.
Unwrap Kisses. Line sheet with saltines.
Put butter and sugar in pan; bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture evenly over crackers. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Immediately spread (unmelted) Kisses or bits evenly over crackers.
As chocolate melts, spread chocolate evenly.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cool in fridge; cut into squares.

title: apple salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice to coat apples.
Mix all ingredients with enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Pour into serving bowl and sprinkle a few nuts on top.

title: asian chicken wrap
directions: Place flour tortillas on work surface.
Divide and layer sliced carrot, squash, scallions, red peppers and chicken in the center of each tortilla.
Roll up tortilla, enclosing filling. Slice in half.

title: pineapple-peach marmalade
directions: Pare, pit and chop peaches fine.
Simmer very slowly until quite thick, stirring often.
Add pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until mixture is quite thick and seal in hot glasses.
This makes about 5 pints of cooked marmalade.

title: world's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and oil together. Add remaining ingredients in order given. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken-kluski-noodles
directions: Place noodles in flat casserole dish.
Place cut up chicken on top.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Combine soup and water; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/3 hours.

title: my grandmother's real pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine at number 7 speed on mixer.
Add sugar gradually while continuing to cream mixture.
Add one egg at a time, beating for 2 minutes after each addition.
Reduce speed to number 4 and add flour gradually, scraping sides with a rubber spatula.
Add vanilla and beat at number 7 for 1 minute.
Pour batter into a large tube pan which has been greased and floured. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Arrange alternate layers of cheese and macaroni, beginning with macaroni and ending with cheese.
Stir salt and nutmeg into milk; pour into one corner of casserole.
Drizzle melted butter on top of casserole.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour, until brown and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: amy's zucchini quiche
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble over bottom of 9-inch unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Pour in cheese, zucchini, onion and egg mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add pineapple alternately with flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat well. Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together in saucepan and cook 5 minutes.
Mix eggs, other Season-All and pepper and beat well. Dip meat into egg mixture.
Roll in crumbs.
Cook in oil until brown.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over meat and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake 1 hour.

title: tuna broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter; add onions and cook until wilted.
Add flour; toss with onions until coated.
Gradually stir in milk until mixture is smooth.
Add broccoli (broken in chunks), salt and chervil.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and broccoli separates.
Add tuna in chunks, sour cream and parsley.
Heat to serving temperature.
(Do not boil!) Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Mash hot potatoes and add cream cheese in pieces, then add butter.
Beat well until all is mixed.
Add sour cream.
Add eggs, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
When fluffy, place in greased 9-inch casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix
all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 3 hours.

title: peanut butter crumb cake
directions: *Use 3/4 cup milk and 2 teaspoons vinegar; let set 5 minutes.

title: bite size venison
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot set on medium and cook 4 hours or until done.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all (except powdered sugar).
Form circles or small crescent shapes.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Roll each in the 1/2 cup powdered sugar.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Trim off and discard excess fat from meat.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Brown on all sides in a large heavy saucepan.
Add onions and saute until they are golden brown.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and green peppers.
Cover and cook 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining paprika.
Serve with cooked rice, wide noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill and serve. You will be the hit of the picnic or barbecue.

title: icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate and water.
Remove from heat; add sugar and yolks one at a time.
Then add flavoring and then beaten whites and cream.
Line dish with ladyfingers.
Pour in filling and set in refrigerator overnight.
Serve topped with whipped cream. Serves 12.

title: pudding finger paint
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
When food stuffs are used in this manner, explain to the children:
"Today we are finger painting with pudding.
Another day we will have it for snack." All finger paints should be stored tightly in covered jars and in a cool place.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir scallop potato mix into meat.
Add dried potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients; stir well.
Cook for about 1 hour, until vegetables are tender.

title: easy no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, oil and eggs; mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Place in greased bowl.
Chill, covered, for 2 hours or longer.
Shape into rolls. Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375°
for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
May store dough in refrigerator for up to 5 days.

title: mexican artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes!
EASY.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In saucepan, blend the egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar, gelatin, water and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until it boils and begins to thicken a little.
Add lemon peel.
Place in a pan of ice water or chill in refrigerator until the mixture mounds when dropping from spoon.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until almost stiff.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until stiff and flaky.
Fold in the lemon mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: tomato, green pepper, potato medley
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion. Stir in potatoes. Cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 10 minutes longer until potatoes and peppers are cooked.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients all together and chill.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and corn syrup in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches 300° on candy thermometer or hard-crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring and flavoring; mix well.
Pour into well-greased cookie pans; cool, enough to touch.
Cut with scissors into bite size pieces; dust with powdered sugar.
Store in airtight containers.

title: hot smokies
directions: Soak sausages in barbecue and hot sauce for 2 hours or overnight.
Add jelly and heat to small boil for approximately 45 minutes.
Keep warm and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli.
Keep just the buds.
Mix broccoli, onion, shredded cheese and crumbled bacon in large bowl.
Mix mayo, vinegar and sugar in small bowl and add to broccoli mixture. Marinate for at least 8 hours before serving.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and oleo in double boiler.
Mix together cake mix and 1/2 cup evaporated milk (batter will be thick).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread half cake mixture in pan.
Bake 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with caramel.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Use a teaspoon and put the remaining cake mix on top. Spread carefully.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cake will not look done.
Let set 8 to 12 hours before serving.
Delicious!

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, soda and cinnamon.
Use 1 cup flour over fruit and nuts and mix well.
Then mix other part with liquid.
Add brandy slowly to liquid.
Stir liquid part into fruit mixture.

title: apple-nut coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Fold into mixture the nuts, coconut and apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Glaze while hot.

title: french baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425° to 450° (with oven rack in middle of oven).
Dip quartered potatoes into olive oil and Worcestershire sauce mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and season.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes, until golden brown and tender.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cut up fryer and remove skin.
Peel red potatoes and cut into large bite-size chunks.
Peel carrots and slice in thin slices. Layer carrots in large iron skillet; add chopped potatoes over carrots, covering bottom of skillet.
Cover both sides of each piece of chicken well with French's seasoned salt.
Place chicken on top of carrots and potatoes.
Add pats of butter on top of each chicken piece, covering larger pieces with 2 to 3 pats.
Place cover on skillet and place in 450° oven.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Check once during baking to add margarine, so chicken and vegetables stay moist.
Serve with English peas.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with a layer of whole crackers. Mix pudding and milk with Cool Whip.
Spread half of this on crackers, another layer of crackers, then remainder of pudding, then a layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours; top with topping.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, onion, green chilies and chicken.
Put a layer of crushed Doritos in bottom of pan. Put a layer of soup mixture, layer of Doritos and then cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix eggs and butter.
Add sugar, milk, salt, corn meal and vanilla.
Cook in raw shell at 350° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: four way delight
directions: Mix in a 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish all ingredients.
Press evenly in bottom of dish and brown at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions, adding walnuts to batter. Bake in two layers and cool completely.
Split cooled layers horizontally.
Mix sour cream, Cool Whip and icing and spread on each layer.
Place sliced bananas on filling.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: pecan rice
directions: Toast pecans in oven at 250° for 15 minutes or until golden. Chop coarsely.
Cook rice.
When ready to serve, coat pecans in butter in skillet.
Add rice and toss.
Salt and pepper.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Melt 2/3 of the margarine in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Empty in hash browns; sprinkle onion on top.
Sprinkle on the Cheddar cheese.
Mix sour cream, soup and pepper and spread on top of cheese.
Melt remaining margarine and toss corn flakes in it; cover the casserole with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.
(Could also use cream of mushroom or celery soup.)

title: juana's barbecue halibut
directions: Mix together and baste on fish as it cooks.
Barbecue (grill) fish until it flakes easily with a fork.
Makes enough for 4 to 6 fillets.

title: three cheese pie
directions: Mix cheese, onion and flour.
Spread in greased pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches) or quiche dish (9 x 2-inches).
Beat eggs slightly; beat in milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over cheese mixture.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until set for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes; arrange tomato slices around edge of pie, overlapping slices slightly.
Makes 8 servings; 230 calories per serving.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine
cream	cheese,
cup
butter
and flour in medium size mixing bowl.	Chill, covered, 1 hour.
Shape into 24 (1-inch)
balls.
Press each dough ball over bottom and up sides of	ungreased
miniature
muffin pans.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place fruit in 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Stir in sugar.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
When cake is done, remove from oven and punch holes all over the top with a wooden spoon or fork.

title: kidney bean relish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except kidney beans, well.
Add kidney beans.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate until served.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: oven-roasted sauced spareribs
directions: Leave ribs whole or cut into serving pieces.
Place in a large shallow pan.
Roast at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix well, form into loaf and bake, covered with foil, for about 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and brown.

title: luciatas
directions: Brown beef in deep skillet or pan.
Add garlic, chopped fine. Cook on low for 5 minutes.
Add tomato juice and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve individually over crushed Fritos.
Top with cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow creme with softened cream cheese until smooth.

title: black beans with rice(low-fat)
directions: Rinse beans.
In a 4-quart Dutch oven, combine black beans and water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Remove from heat, cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans.
In the same pot, combine the beans, broth, chopped onions, green pepper, celery, garlic, bay leaves, oregano, salt, red pepper and cumin.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until black beans are tender, stirring in undrained tomatoes the last 15 minutes of cooking.
Discard bay leaves.
Mash beans slightly.
Stir in lemon juice.
Serve atop rice.
Raw chopped onion is good; also a spoonful of nonfat sour cream.

title: garlic and potato soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, brown bacon until crisp, remove and drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 to 3 tablespoons bacon fat.
Saute onion in bacon fat.
Add garlic and saute.
Add stock, potatoes and cayenne pepper and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer until potatoes are tender (about 15 minutes).
With a potato masher, crush potatoes to achieve a creamy consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with chives and bacon sprinkled on top.

title: squash delight
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Add butter and mash.
Mix eggs, sugar, mayonnaise, nuts, salt, pepper and cheese.
Add to squash.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Dot with butter.
Decorate with pecans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil; let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 1 quart.

title: congo squares
directions: First, beat eggs well; add brown sugar, melted Crisco, vanilla and dry ingredients a little at a time.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes in 13 X 9 X 2 pan.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and bell pepper in oil.
Add soups and tomatoes.
Simmer until hot and mixed well.
In a casserole dish, place crumbled chips.
Add chicken to soup mixture; stir well and pour over chips.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Cook at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies(from candicci's restaurant)
directions: Mix oats, flour, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Set aside.
With an electric mixer on medium speed, cream butter, sugars and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips by hand.
Add butter mixture to oat mixture.
Mix by hand until dough is formed. (Dough will appear crumbly, but keep mixing.)
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.
Makes a flat, thin crisp cookie.

title: microwave chocolate mousse
directions: Combine cocoa and oil until smooth in a large glass mixing bowl. Soften gelatin in milk for 5 minutes in a glass cup. Microwave on High (full power) until warm, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Add gelatin-milk mixture to cocoa along with 1/3 cup sugar and salt. Microwave on Medium (1/2 power) for 5 minutes. Stir and continue cooking on Medium until slightly thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes. Beat egg yolks slightly. Add about 1/2 cup of hot mixture.
Stir in vanilla until mixture is well blended. Press plastic wrap onto surface. Chill until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl until foamy.

Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar until stiff peaks hold. Gently fold egg whites and whipped cream into chocolate mixture. Spoon into individual dessert dishes or 9-inch baked pie shell. Chill until set.
Garnish with additional whipped cream, if desired. Serves 8.

title: company cheese cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and press into bottom and up 2/3-inch of sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix eggs, cream cheese, sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Add sour cream. Pour into crust and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or just until set. Cool.
Chill 4 to 5 hours.
Filling will be soft.
Serves 12 to 16.
Add
a can of Comstock cherry pie filling on top of cake after it cools for a wonderful cherry cheesecake.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries; grind with 1/2 the rind from the orange. Mix with sugar and let stand several hours or overnight.
Dissolve jello in boiling water with salt and vinegar.
Let chill, then add celery, nut meats and apples.
Add to the cranberries and chopped oranges.
Let set.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: mulled cider
directions: Simmer apple cider, whole allspice, cinnamon stick and cloves for 15 minutes; strain.
Add lemon juice and orange juice just before serving.

title: mexican crescent bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef with onion and seasoning mix. Drain. Stir in refried beans.
Separate dinner rolls into two rectangles.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, ungreased, press over bottom and 1/2 sides up to form crust sealing perforations.
Spoon meat mixture over crust.
Sprinkle with olives.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix soup, water and flour until smooth. Combine with remaining ingredients in a covered roasting pan.
Bake for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Will keep in refrigerator 1 to 2 weeks.

title: mom's solar banana bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking soda 3 times.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix together.
Add bananas and eggs to flour mixture and blend (this batter should not be over mixed).
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pound loaves.

title: south of the border
directions: Mix together beans and seasoning; spread into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread sour cream on top of that and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese starts to bubble.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dog bones for fido
directions: In a large bowl pour hot water over oleo.
Stir in powdered milk, salt and egg.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well. Knead 3 to 4 minutes, adding more flour as needed to make "stiff" dough.
Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out.
Bake on greased cookie sheet until hard, approximately 50 minutes.
Cool and dry out thoroughly.

title: summer lemon jello salad
directions: Prepare lemon Jell-O by package directions using large bowl. Chill until almost set. Stir in all finely chopped vegetables. Chill until set. Serve on bed of lettuce, topped with small dab of mayonnaise for garnish.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the hot water.
Melt the cream cheese in it.
Add vanilla and cool.
Mix in the 7-Up, pineapple and nuts; chill.

title: mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook pasta; drain and place in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Set aside.

title: autumn pork chops
directions: In medium skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil. Add chops and cook 10 minutes or until browned. Set chops aside. Pour off fat.
Add soup, apple juice, mustard, honey and pepper. Heat to boil. Return chops to pan and reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 10 minutes or until chops are no longer pink.

title: louisiana rice dressing
directions: Boil livers and giblets until tender.
Place giblets in a food processor. Chop until fine.
Chop livers coarsely with a knife. Saute onions, garlic and celery in oil. Add ground beef and cook until done. Add all of the other ingredients, except parsley. Cook approximately 1 hour.
Add a small amount of water to avoid sticking. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with cooked rice.

title: mexican turkey casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine turkey,
soup, milk and chilies.
Heat slowly, stirring until bubbling.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the corn chips on the bottom of a 2 quart casserole dish.
Pour in half of the turkey mixture, half of onions, and half of each of the cheeses.
Layer another 1/3 of the corn chips, remaining turkey mixture, onions and cheeses.
Top with remaining corn chips.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; let stand about 5 minutes.
Combine flour, sugar and salt in a medium sized nonmetal bowl and stir well.
Gradually stir in 2 cups warm water.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Cover starter loosely with plastic wrap or cheesecloth; let stand in warm place (85°) for 72 hours, stirring 2 to 3 times daily.
Place fermented mixture in refrigerator and stir once a day.
Use within 11 days.

title: fudge squares
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add butter and cool.
Beat eggs, add sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to eggs with nuts and vanilla.
Then add chocolate mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares while warm and roll in powdered sugar.
Double the recipe if you like and pour into a long cookie sheet.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix butter (melted) and cheese.
Add flour, flakes and pepper. Knead well with hands.
Roll out marble size balls.
Press with fork.
(Dip fork in water each time to prevent sticking.)
Bake at 325° on greased cookie sheet 30 minutes or until crisp.

title: pasta with steamed veggies
directions: Steam vegetables or saute in butter until still crisp.
Add mushrooms the last minute.
Cook pasta according to directions and drain.
Add butter, whipping cream, vegetables and seasonings. Toss well.
Serve warm with cheese sprinkled on top.
Serves 8.

title: quick skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil or shortening.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in water, tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, Heinz 57 sauce and macaroni.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until macaroni is tender.
Makes 5 servings.

title: karen's turkey surprises
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the biscuits.
Put into deep casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Take out of oven and place the biscuits on top of casserole.
Heat oven to 400° and bake 10 to 15 minutes, until biscuits are golden brown.

title: jamie's grilled zucchini
directions: Toss squash and onion with olive oil in large bowl.
Pour vegetables onto flat grilling pan or heavy aluminum foil over medium flame on barbecue grill.
Spread zucchini slices flat and sift garlic salt to taste (about 1 to 2 teaspoons) over vegetables. Turn squash pieces when brown on bottom side.
Stir onion pieces several times.
Remove vegetables after browning both sides of the zucchini.

title: sharon's strawberry-banana jello
directions: Dissolve jello in water; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to jello.
Pour half of mixture in pan and spread 1 pint sour cream over top, then spread remaining strawberry mixture.

title: depression potato soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter or margarine until slightly brown.
Add cubed potatoes, water to cover and salt.
Cook until tender and add enough milk to make it soupy.
Thicken by making a paste of flour and milk or you can mash some of the potatoes against the side of the pan.
Add vinegar or lemon juice.
Taste it.
Add pepper.
If you want, add cooked green beans.

title: punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, Kool-Aid, lemonade and water.
Add sugar to taste.
Just before serving, add ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: low carb chicken enchiladas
directions: Spray 8 x 8 dish with vegetable spray. Set aside.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Mix potatoes, water and onion.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add white sauce.
Season to taste.
Heat to boiling.
Top with paprika.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown burger in skillet.
Add zucchini, peppers and onion. Cook until tender.
Drain.
Add egg and milk.
Put half of mixture into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle half of crumbs and cheese. Add rest of mixture then remaining crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add mashed bananas and oil and stir until all is mixed.
Add buttermilk last.
Pour in 2 small loaf pans (greased).
Bake at 300° until brown.
May be frozen.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut and vegetables together.
Heat sugar, oil and vinegar.
Let cool, then pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: crab dip
directions: Rinse and drain crabmeat.
Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
When crabmeat is well drained; put on oblong plate, shape cream cheese over it.
Just before serving, pour chilled cocktail sauce over.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix cake batter as directed, add drained oranges.
Bake as directed on box.
When cake is done, drain pineapple, saving juice.
Pour the juice on the cake and let cool.

title: tutti-fruitti ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, salt, sugar and ice cream mix together.
Add Pet milk and cook until it thickens on spoon.
Add cherries, pineapple, whole milk and vanilla.
Put all ingredients into a 1-gallon freezer and freeze.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: pa's cookies
directions: You will need aluminum foil or tinfoil, cookie sheet covered with foil, refrigerator or freezer, basting brush and saucepan.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast in oil until done.
Slice onion and pepper rings over chicken that has been put in casserole dish.
Slice potatoes over onions and pepper rings.
Pour mushroom soup over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese vegetables with rice
directions: Bring water with salt to boil and cook rice about 45 minutes on low heat.
Fry carrots and peas for 1 to 2 minutes, then add cauliflower and onion.
Cook 1 more minute.
Mix chicken seasoning and cornstarch in the cold water.
Pour into frypan with vegetables.
Add the almonds and pour over cooked rice.

title: blueberry pudding dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Layer pudding, cubed pound cake, peaches and blueberries.
Chill until time to serve.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Mash to form a crust.
Cool in freezer for 10 minutes.
Add chocolate chips.
Add coconut.
Add other chips.
Pour over sweetened condensed milk. Microwave for 5 - 7 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain the pineapple and peaches.
Mix all ingredients, then pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° until bubbly (20 to 25 minutes).

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in 3 or 4 quart saucepan over low heat. Remove from
heat;
let
cool.
Add
sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt;
add	to first mixture.
Mix well; chill.
Form 1-inch balls,
roll
in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheets
inches apart.
Bake in moderately hot oven, 375°, for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Use large cucumbers.
Peel off green rind.
Take out seed and cut in 1/4-inch slices or 1-inch cubes.
Soak in 1 cup lime water for 24 hours.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add corn bread last. Bake in 400° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole #1
directions: Cover with foil (shiny side out).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
If onions need browning, take foil off for a few minutes.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix by hand, adding sugar a little at a time.
After being mixed, spread into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Let set for approximately 1 hour.
Cut in sizes you may want to serve.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, then add sugars and oil. Measure and sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to egg mixture; mix well.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and Rice Krispies; blend well.
Drop on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Lay chicken breasts in bottom of casserole; put cheese on as next layer.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Pour soup and water mixture over top.
Press stuffing mix into liquid for moisture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute chicken, celery and onion in butter.
Then add all ingredients into large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: lemon-baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Combine oil, lemon juice, oregano or tarragon and garlic powder and brush on chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove cover.
Brush again with oil-lemon mixture.
Continue baking, uncovered, 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika before serving.
Contains 225 calories per serving.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together softened butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat 4 minutes. In another bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to butter mixture (you will probably need to mix this with your hands).
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: crispy lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.

title: zucchini corn
directions: In a large skillet, melt the margarine and saute the onion until browned.
Add the zucchini and corn.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, cream the butter and 1 1/2 cups of
sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough into balls using rounded teaspoonful of dough for each.
Combine 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon; coat balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are set, about 14 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain well.
Add taco seasoning to meat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Chop lettuce, tomato and onion. Put in separate container as well as grated cheese.
Put all ingredients on table and create your own salad with the Fritos and meat.

title: heath bar ice cream torte
directions: Line 10-inch Spring Form pan (bottom and sides) with lady fingers.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl, with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Freeze over night. Delicious!

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add dates and heat about 3 minutes. Stir in nuts cereal and vanilla. Shape into small balls. Roll each one in coconut.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop up bell pepper and onion for the amount desired to taste.
Crush cup crackers. Add egg, Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine or mix with hands until blended well.
Place in shallow loaf pan or shallow pan and form into loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin surprise
directions: Mix together pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and spices. Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over this mixture.
Put 2 cups chopped pecans over cake mix.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over pecans.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut into squares.
May be served with Cool Whip.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix ham, 4 ounces cream cheese, 1/2 cup Miracle Whip, 1/2 cup chopped almonds, onion and pickle relish.
Chill and shape in a ball.
In a small bowl; mix 1/4 cup Miracle Whip and 4 ounces cream cheese.
Spread on ball; cover with almonds.
Chill.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Preheat oven according to cake package directions.

title: sausage pineapple appetizer(microwave)
directions: Microwave jelly and mustard on High for 2 minutes, stirring twice to blend.
Cut Smok-Y-Links into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add pineapple and Smok-Y-Links to sauce.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring twice during cooking.
Serve hot.

title: classic walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine first six ingredients; blend well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Arrange walnuts on top.
Bake in lower third of oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake an additional 35 to 45 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool completely.
Makes 8 servings. Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Bake time:
50 to 60 minutes.

title: english hot slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat the mixture to boiling point.
Pour over shredded cabbage and toss quickly.
Put a tight lid on pot (to hold heat) and keep warm until served.
Serve within 10 minutes after preparing.

title: layered pizza dip
directions: Layer in ungreased 9-inch pie plate/pan in order listed. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly bubbly.
Serve with bagel chips or assorted crackers.

title: african chop suey
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Drain off any grease.
Add soups, water, celery and rice.
Put into sprayed baking dish and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: muffins that taste like doughnuts
directions: (If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.)

title: microwave chili
directions: Place ground meat in 3-quart casserole.
Cook by microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes of cooking.
Remove meat from microwave and set aside.
In small casserole or 2-cup glass measure, combine onion, garlic and green pepper with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Cover and microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cooked veggies to heat.
Stir in undrained kidney beans, chili powder and salt.
Cover container.
Place in microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium and continue cooking 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets about 25 to 30 minutes, until done.
Remove from heat and drain water.
Let cool before dicing. Sprinkle potatoes with sugar and vinegar.
Add celery, onion, pickles and salt.
Stir gently to combine.
Add mayonnaise by folding into mixture.
Add sliced eggs.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients, except cheese.
Line pan with heavy waxed paper.
Place 1/2 cup cheese in bottom of pan; spread evenly.
Cover with half of meat loaf mixture.
Repeat with remaining cheese and meat layers.
Bake at 350° for about an hour. Allow loaf to stand for 10 minutes before turning out on a platter.

title: minute rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes or serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg; serve warm.
(For chilled pudding, place plastic wrap or wax paper on surface of hot pudding.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Stir before serving.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.)
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: microwave easy chicken rice supper
directions: In a 3-quart casserole mix rice, soup, water and carrots. Place chicken pieces on top of rice mixture, arranging the thickest sides of pieces toward outside of casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika or herbs.
Cover casserole with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Uncover and rearrange chicken pieces if certain areas are overcooking.
Re-cover and microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in large jar and shake thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep for months.

title: luscious cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Drain can of crushed pineapple when cake is done.
While still hot, pour pineapple juice over cake.
Poke a few holes in cake with toothpick.
Let cake cool.
Mix drained pineapple, Cool Whip, and instant pudding.
Spread over cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour, cloves, allspice, cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
Add applesauce and baking soda last.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Spoon into muffin pans lined with cupcake papers.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Lay in dish and pour 1/2 of pudding, then 1/2 of fruit, then Cool Whip.
Add more Twinkies, pudding and fruit and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: cream of blue cheese soup
directions: Bring chicken stock to a gentle boil. Add grated carrot and chopped onion, salt, and pepper: simmer gently for one hour. Add paprika and butter; simmer gently for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, blend flour and milk until smooth; stir into chicken stock and cook until smooth and thickened. Then add Blue cheese, Worcestershire, and liquid hot-pepper seasoning. Continue to simmer gently until well blended (about 15 minutes). Serve hot in small soup bowls.

title: white corn bread
directions: Mix and sift all dry ingredients together; pour in buttermilk and stir thoroughly; then add egg. Beat well. Pour into hot greased pan and bake in a hot over, 450 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Put all the ingredients in a casserole dish with lid and bake at 400°, for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 28 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove and let cool completely on wire racks.
Stir 1/2 cup pecans into Cream Cheese Frosting, if desired, or reserve them to sprinkle over top of frosted cake. Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers in red or green peppers for serving bowl.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: At room temperature, mix the ingredients together with hands. Make balls and bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pecan logs
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, creme and vanilla.
Knead until smooth (mixture will be dry).
Shape into six 4 1/2 in. x 1 1/4 in. logs.
Chill overnight.
In the top of a double boiler over boiling water, cook and stir caramels and water until smooth.
Dip logs into caramel.
Roll in pecans.
Chill for 2 hours.
Cut into 1/3 in. slices.
Yield:
about 6 1/2 doz.

title: easiest pie
directions: Melt butter in a 8 x 8 inch dish. Mix together sugar, flour, milk and stir until smooth. Pour over melted butter, do not stir. Pour fruit over milk mixture, do not stir. Bake 325° for 35 minutes.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Arrange carrots in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 4 to 8 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.
Remove from steamer and keep warm.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Beat in rest of ingredients until smooth.
Spoon onto hot greased griddle.
Turn pancakes as soon as they are puffed and full.

title: buckeyes candy
directions: Mix and roll in small balls.
Refrigerate one hour.
Melt chocolate and dip balls in chocolate.
Put on wax paper.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift
all
dry ingredients together into a 10-inch cake pan. Make
3 depressions and into the first, put the shortening.
In the next depression, put the vinegar and in the last depression, put
the vanilla.
Pour the water over the entire pan.
Stir with a fork until all the ingredients are moist; do not beat.
Bake
in same pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Leave in pan and ice to taste.

title: cocktail crab spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce with juice from crab.
Mix until soft.
Spread on plate and top with crumbled crab.
Mix chili sauce and horseradish to taste; spread over crab meat and garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: pete's peanut brittle(yield: makes 3.5 lbs.)
directions: 1. Butter 2 heavy large baking sheets (if your cookie sheets are nonstick this is not necessary).

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil the bouillon cubes, water, potatoes, celery, carrots and onion for 20 minutes.
Add the broccoli or cauliflower and cook until tender.
Add the soup and cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: banana pudding - the low-fat way!(servings:  12)
directions: Beat pudding mix and 4 cups of milk about 2 minutes with mixer on low speed.
Pour in Eagle Brand milk and blend.
Add Cool Whip; blend.
Cover bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan with wafers. Slice 4 bananas and place on top of wafers.
Add half of the filling.
Place the remainder of the wafers on top
of this (on bottom only this time).
Place the other bananas on top.
Then add remainder of pudding mix.
Refrigerate for 5 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each one.
Sift dry ingredients, then add to egg mixture.
Add strawberries; stir in pecans.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pans.

title: apricot tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keeps indefinitely in an airtight container.
To serve, add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of boiling water.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water overnight.
Rinse well with cold water and drain.
Cook in other ingredients, mixed together, for 5 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese (Muenster) in one large bowl. Pour mixture into greased pie plate or quiche dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with Muenster cheese at end until melted.

title: cherry-o pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Put in graham cracker crust and top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate before serving and keep cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter.
Add mushrooms.
Add beef broth and cook until tender.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Add sour cream to beef mixture just before serving. Pour over noodles.

title: cranberry crunch salad
directions: Slice the cranberries.
Add cranberries, sugar and pineapple and let it sit in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, add marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: mom's caramel popcorn balls
directions: Pop about 1 1/2 or 2 cups of popcorn.
Separate the popped kernels from the unpopped.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to make 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into jello in large bowl until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes, stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Refrigerate until firm. Serves 10.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In casserole dish, combine all ingredients, except butter and crackers.
Mix crackers and butter until well blended.
Sprinkle over top of macaroni mixture and bake until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix cheese, onion and chicken in large bowl.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup.
Dip tortillas in hot oil until soft.
Place spoonful of cheese mixture in tortilla and roll up.
Place single layer in pan.
Top with sour cream.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, until sour cream is bubbling.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash dried mushrooms.
Soak overnight.
In morning, cook mushrooms in the water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly for 2 hours or more.

title: savory beef
directions: Brown onions
and
meat, which has been cut in cubes in serving pieces.
Mix dry ingredients; sprinkle over meat.
Add bouillon, water, vinegar and catsup.
Stir until well blended; cover.
Simmer
1/2 hours until tender.	(If you use canned meat it does not need to simmer as long.)

title: creamy coffee punch
directions: Combine coffee and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Chill thoroughly.
Combine coffee mixture, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring gently.
Ladle into serving cups.
If desired, top each with whipped cream.
Yields about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: In a large saucepan, cook spaghetti in boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes; drain.
Stir butter into hot pasta.
Stir in beaten egg and Parmesan cheese.
Form spaghetti into a "crust" in a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Spread with cottage cheese.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soups, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, 1/2 Parmesan cheese and garlic salt together in large bowl.
Pour into greased casserole dish (2 quart).
Dot with margarine and sprinkle top with remainder of Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: con queso dipjust like casa ole!
directions: Cut cheese into small chunks and melt in microwave. Be careful, it will burn.

title: pepperoni roll
directions: Thaw dough.
Roll into 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Melt butter and brush on dough.
Put pepperoni, salami, Mozzarella and oregano on dough. Roll up.
Lightly butter roll.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown.
Serve warm or cold or freeze.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
In frypan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
To reserved drippings, add onion and cook until tender.
Add flour, bouillon, salt and pepper; stir until smooth.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Bring to boil.
Slice warm potatoes and add to sauce mixture along with crumbled bacon.
Toss lightly to coat.
Heat and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add other ingredients, ending with bacon fat.
Use an iron skillet if you have one.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef and macaroni(preparation time: 5 minutes.  serves 4 to 6.)
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil or in nonstick pan.
Add all ingredients until done.
Top with cheese.

title: shortcut chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cook chicken breasts in skillet until browned.	Remove from skillet.
To skillet add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil and cook until cheese is melted and all mixed.	Place chicken in baking dish.
