Pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: hot sauce fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and skin (if you want to).
Place in a large stainless steel or glass bowl (may stain plastic).
Pour Louisiana hot sauce over and let marinate several hours.
I have used it in 30 minutes, but it has a better flavor if marinated longer.
Take chicken pieces out of sauce and roll them in self-rising flour. Coat them good.
Fry in preheated hot oil.
Cook until done (30 minutes).
Done when thick piece is pierced with a fork (deeply) and juice runs clear.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and oatmeal. Mix well and drop by spoonful onto pan greased with butter. Cool.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, chili powder and garlic powder.
Add soups and tomatoes;
heat.
Layer
in baking dish: chips, meat and cheese.
Bake
at
for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes more.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat milk (with cinnamon stick if desired) until bubbles begin to appear around edge of pan.
Stir sugar and salt into eggs.
Add hot milk slowly to egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Return to double boiler and cook over low heat, while stirring, until mixture coats spoon.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired. Chill and serve from pitcher.

title: italian chocolate cookies
directions: Cream shortening and powdered sugar.
Add eggs, beating well. Add cocoa, cloves, cinnamon, milk and baking powder.
Add enough flour to hold ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broiled banana cake
directions: Cream
sugar and shortening;
beat in eggs and bananas. Mix dry ingredients; add banana mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Put
in oblong pan in moderate oven.
When done enough to	hold
up
frosting,
remove
from
oven and spread topping on cake.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan; keep a few crumbs for topping.

title: leek soup
directions: Wash leeks.
Wash leeks and once more for good measure.
Melt margarine in large pot.
Add leeks and saute for 5 to 10 minutes until tender.
Add potatoes, bouillon cubes and water.
Cover and allow to cook until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally. Mix together sour cream and cornstarch and add to soup to thicken. Salt, pepper and lemon juice are added to taste.
Ham is added in the last 5 minutes or so to allow to heat through.
Eggs are halved and floated in soup when served.

title: spam-pineapple rice casserole
directions: Cook first five ingredients together until clear and thick, stirring constantly.
Add last three ingredients and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into saucepan and heat.
Dissolve jello in pineapple.
Add 2 cups buttermilk and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
(May use orange, lemon or lime jello.)

title: german pancakes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Place in mixing bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Fry on hot skillet turning once.

title: fruit cocktail(southern indiana style)
directions: Combine orange juice and bananas.
Add remaining ingredients, except pudding mix.
Stir, then add pudding mix.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Melt butter.
Dip eggplant in mixture of crumbs and salt.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Spoon sauce on each slice and sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: holiday breakfast
directions: Mix milk, salt, mustard and eggs.
Pour over other ingredients, tossing lightly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar together.
Add flour and pecans.
Form into small finger shaped cookies.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Roll each cookie in granulated sugar while still warm.

title: jimmy carter pudding
directions: For first layer, mix 1 cup flour, stick of oleo, and 2/3 cup salted chopped peanuts. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. For second layer, mix 1/3 c. peanut butter, 8 oz. pkg. cream cheese, 1 c. powdered sugar, 1 c. whipped cream. Spread over first layer. For third layer, mix boxes of puddings with milk and spread over second layer. Finally spread whipped cream to cover top of pudding. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of baking dish.
Add next 6 ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Combine all ingredients in order; mix well.
Pour in well-greased 10-inch glass pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to an hour, or until golden brown.

title: swiss cheese and veggies in pitas
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Separate 3 pita breads along cut sides to form pockets.
Arrange some salad greens and veggie mixture in pockets.

title: good and plenty salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar. In another bowl, blend fruit, nuts and whipped topping. Fold in cream cheese and sugar; freeze. Take out of freezer 1/2 to 1 hour before serving.

title: nut goodie bar
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips and peanut butter. Spread half of this mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate until cool.
Mix melted margarine, milk and pudding mix in pan.
Bring to boil; remove and add powdered sugar and maple flavoring.
Beat until smooth.
Spread onto first layer of cooled chocolate mix.
Add peanuts to rest of the chocolate mixture.
Spread this on top of second layer.
Refrigerate, then cut into small pieces.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes until leaves are limp, then drain.

Combine ground beef, salt and pepper, regular rice, chopped onion, egg, nutmeg, sage and thyme. Place meat portions into cabbage leaves. Roll and fasten with string or a toothpick. Brown in 3 tablespoons oil.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish. Brush cracker crumbs on top with butter and brown.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue lima beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Leave 2 to 3 tablespoons bacon grease.
Fry onion in grease.
Add flour to thicken.
Add tomato soup and stir.
Add vinegar, sugar and garlic salt.
Add enough water to make medium thick sauce.
Crumble and add 1/2 of the bacon.
Pour sauce over lima beans in 2-quart greased casserole.
Mix lightly.
Top with rest of bacon, crumbled.
Bake about 30 minutes on 350°.
I usually cover it until last 5 minutes.

title: orange frost
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and process on high until smooth and frothy.

title: old-fashioned cabbage rolls
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
In a large kettle or Dutch oven, cook cabbage in boiling, salted water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove outer leaves when softened; return to boiling water as necessary to obtain 12 leaves.
Drain.
Remove thick center vein from leaves.

title: cheesy-topped chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops in hot oil about 10 minutes; drain. Transfer chops to an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine; stir in flour.
Add milk and cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir 1/2 the thickened mixture into beaten egg; return to saucepan.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese, onion and pepper.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of mixture atop each chop.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until meat is done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chess tarts
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into tart shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: "better than sex" cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
Poke holes in hot cake with a straw and pour topping over cake.
When cake is cool, cover topping with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with the crushed Heath bars or chocolate sprinkles.

title: candy walnuts or pecans
directions: Boil together to soft ball stage (236°), stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 4 to 5 cups nuts. Stir until covered well.
Turn out quickly onto waxed paper and separate nuts.
Let sit until hardened.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and mix with 1/2 stick melted margarine and sour cream.
Mix onion, cheese, soup, salt and pepper and add to hash browns.
Mix melted margarine with corn flakes.
Pour over top of hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Pour apple juice in a frying pan over low heat; stir in cinnamon and salt.
Add sweet potatoes.
Cook over low heat, turning sweet potatoes several times until they are well coated and most of juice is absorbed (about 6 minutes).
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus and ham
directions: Drain asparagus and layer in buttered 8 x 8 pyres dish.
Add ham, soup, cheese and breadcrumbs.
Bake 350 until bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni, green pepper and onions.
Stir to coat well.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Pour La Choy sauce on top.

title: diet kapani(quick noodle substitute for soup)
directions: Beat egg with flour.
Pour into boiling chicken broth gradually; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate chicken at least 1 hour, turning often.
Place on broiler pan (lined with foil for easy cleanup).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, basting often, turning once.
Also good on outdoor grill.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Combine the soups, tomatoes, picante sauce, green pepper, onion and chili powder. In a
greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Layer half the tortilla strips, chicken, soup mixture and cheese. Repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water according to package directions; drain.
Combine egg, cottage cheese, Parmesan and meat.
In 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half each of noodles, meat mixture, Mozzarella and spaghetti sauce; repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered in 375° oven for 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add all ingredients together. Mix until smooth. Add poppy seed filling. Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes. Turn batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done. Cool cake 5 to 8 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Cake:
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans.
Prepare batter as directed on package.
Divide batter evenly between pans.
Bake and cool as directed on package.

title: pineapple lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and water in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Cool, then stir in lemon juice.
Serve in glasses half filled with ice cubes. Serves 12.

title: spinach or string beans with tomatoes and spaghetti(spinach all pomodori e spaghetti)
directions: In medium saucepan, saute
garlic in oil.
When lightly brown, add tomatoes,
sauce,
red
pepper,
salt,
parsley and water. Cook for 10
to 12 minutes on medium heat.
Add frozen spinach and cook
an
additional
25 minutes, until spinach is heated thoroughly.
Boil
spaghetti
according
to
package directions. Pour cooked spinach over top of the spaghetti and toss thoroughly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple duckling
directions: Remove excess fat from duckling and place in a shallow dish. Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Combine pineapple juice, soy sauce, ginger, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over duckling and marinate 3 hours or more, turning duckling occasionally.
Remove duckling.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Stir in marinade and add duckling.
Reduce heat to 212°.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove duckling. Combine cornstarch and water. Pour into cooker, stirring constantly until gravy has thickened. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: garlic pasta salad
directions: While noodles are cooking, combine vegetables in mixing bowl. Drain cooked noodles and toss with vegetable mixture.
Add dressing; cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour and pepper.
Add melted butter and brown beef. Add onion and mushrooms.
Brown.
Add 1 can beef broth and cook until tender for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Last, add 8 ounces sour cream and serve over egg noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
You may add 1/2 cup or more of Blue cheese or other cheese.
Form into shape desired. Chill overnight.
Roll in slivered almonds or chopped pecans.

title: uncle art's chicken in a skillet
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Take chicken out.
Put in other ingredients.
Lay chicken back in.
On top, slice the cheese or add already shredded.
Season with salt.
Cook 30 minutes, slowly, until done. Put lid on and simmer 10 minutes.

title: pocket pizza
directions: Heat the oven to 425°. Lightly grease a cookie sheet with shortening.

title: garbanzo loaf(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute onions and celery in Pam sprayed frypan until onion turns clear.
Add tomatoes and flour.
Stir until thickened.
Then add this to ingredients and combine it all together.
Place in Pam sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, jello and sugar.
Add water and cook over medium heat until it thickens.
Cool completely.
Stir in strawberries. Pour in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: oven crisp chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Process stuffing until fine crumbs.
Coat chicken with sour cream mixture.
Roll in crumbs.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Drizzle with melted butter and bake for one hour.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal mega batch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In upright mixer bowl, cream butter and sugars. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients into wet ingredients until blended.
(Place wet ingredients in larger bowl before adding wet ingredients; beat by hand.)
Add oatmeal, mix and stir in chips and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 32 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: crowning glory sauce(an excellent sauce for ice cream, pound cake or bread pudding)
directions: Melt sugar in skillet until light brown; cool.
Add butter and stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook until thickened.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup to put on top of cake before baking. Add the rest of the ingredients and put in pan, topping with reserved crumbs. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add beaten egg and melted margarine. Add pecans and nutmeg last.
Cover cookie sheets with aluminum foil and place dough by small teaspoonfuls on foil.
Allow space for cookies to spread as they bake.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven when cookies are golden brown around the edges.

title: pineapple pecan cheese ball
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Gently stir in pineapple, green pepper, onions, salt and 1/2 cup nuts.
Shape into a ball. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Before serving, roll cheese ball in remaining nuts.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: noodle pudding(lochen kugel)
directions: Boil egg noodles according to package directions, drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Top with fresh strawberries in season.

title: appetizer tidbits
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce, meat, bread, egg, onion and salt.
Mix lightly.
Shape into 30 (1-inch) balls.
Brown in oil.
Add remaining barbecue sauce, pineapple chunks, frankfurters, green pepper and water chestnuts.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until meatballs are thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Melt butter in 8 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter over melted butter and add peaches and juice.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain juice off into a large container. Cut cucumbers into slices. Add 5 pounds sugar, vinegar, pickling spice; and onions to vinegar and heat until sugar is dissolved. Stir several times. Add sliced cucumbers and let set 24 hours. Put
in jars.

title: spam, tomato sauce
directions: Melt shortening in a frying pan.
Chop onion and fry until done.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat. Cut Spam in slices and brown.
Place on platter and pour tomato sauce over it.
Serve.
Good on camping trips and hunting trips.

title: potato dish
directions: Cook potatoes whole, then cut into cubes.
In a saucepan, combine cheese and butter.
Stir until melted.
Remove from stove and blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix with potatoes and put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Accent and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice with sugar and water.
Stir in gelatin to dissolve.
Chill until partially congealed.
Fold in cream cheese, then nuts, then Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until well set.
Serve.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Simmer green pepper and onion until tender.
Mix with soft bread cubes and add all the corn.
Beat the eggs with the salt and add to corn mixture.
Spoon into lightly buttered 2 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: lime punch
directions: Fill an ice cube tray with soda so as not to dilute the punch when ice cubes melt.
Mix fluids and add sherbet last.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Add first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add crackers, sprinkle cinnamon in mixture and stir well.
Boil about 2 minutes until crackers look clear.
Pour in pie crust.
Dot with butter. Add top crust; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is brown at 425°.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Blend in blender in the preceeding order and serve with fresh cauliflower, bell peppers, celery, carrot sticks and broccoli.

title: best ever turkey breast
directions: Thaw turkey breast in refrigerator.
Wash and dry well.
Rub outside well with salt and pepper.
Also sprinkle some on the inside.
Fill cavity with chunks of celery and onion.
Wrap breast good and tight with aluminum foil.
Put in crock-pot.
Add 1 cup of water.
Turn to high for about an hour.
Reduce to low and cook all night.
You will have lots of good broth and the turkey breast will be nice and juicy and tender.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and butter together; sprinkle a layer of this on the crust.
Fill with fresh peaches (sliced) and put remaining mixture on the top.
Bake at 350° until peaches are done.

title: country style steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Roll each steak in flour mixture.
Preheat a skillet on medium-high heat and brown steaks on each side.
Remove steaks from pan and place in a baking dish. With remaining flour, make a gravy in the drippings using the water as liquid.
Add cream of mushroom soup to gravy and pour over steaks.
Place sliced onion over steaks; cover with foil. Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given; pour into pie crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish, if desired, with whipped topping.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add eggs, salt, oil and molasses. Mix well.
Mix in flour.
Knead until smooth.
Cover.
Let rise in a warm place until about double.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows.
Add 2 teaspoons green food coloring, vanilla and 5 cups corn flakes.
Let pan stand in hot water.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Add three red hots in center of leaf cookie.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Saute onions in hot oil until soft.
Add meat; stir and cook until meat loses red color.
Pour off fat.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Pour on tomato sauce and water.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve hot over cooked spaghetti. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in balls or patties.
Fry in hot grease.

title: ham hock and lima beans
directions: Place lima beans in a large bowl.
After washing beans well, cover with water; let stand overnight.
Save water which lima beans were soaked.
Place lima beans in good size pot; pour half of the water in lima beans and cook over low heat for over 15 minutes in covered pot.
While beans are cooking, cut onion, celery and carrots into dices; add whole peppercorns, salt and nutmeg.
Put into the bean pot.
Let simmer for another 15 minutes.
Wash ham hocks and put into beans; simmer for 1 hour.
Add rest of water that beans were soaked in if necessary.
Do not overseason.
Cook until ham hocks are well done.
Serves 4.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Combine sugar, flour, 2 eggs and 3 egg yolks, reserving the egg whites.
Beat this mixture (not the whites).
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add milk.
Stir in butter.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Put in crust and bake at 350° until done.
Done when knife placed in center comes out clean.

title: fudge
directions: Mix nuts, powdered sugar and cocoa.
Melt butter and cheese. Add vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together and pat out on wax paper or cookie sheet.
Cut into squares.

title: pizza ryes
directions: Brown sausage or hamburger and drain.
Melt the cheese in same pot.
Stir in salt and sauce.
Spread on rye bread and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Can be baked and reheated in microwave. Can also be frozen and taken out a few at a time.

title: lydia's orange chiffon cake
directions: Beat egg whites together well and add 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Add the rest of the ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Then turn oven to 350° for 5 or 10 minutes.
Cool cake upside down on bottle for 2 hours before releasing cake.
Use 10-inch tube pan.

title: pasta oriental(microwave)
directions: Cook chicken in 2-quart microwavesafe casserole 3 to 7 minutes, breaking up chicken after 3 minutes. Mix in remaining ingredients, but only use 1 cup water. Cook 7 minutes. Let stand 2 minutes. Stir and serve.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: For the crust, mix together the flour and margarine until dough forms.
Spread in an ungreased pizza pan and bake at 350° until crust starts to brown.

title: aunt bessie's brown sugar-nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Add sifted flour and baking powder.
Beat well, then add vanilla and nuts (save some nuts for top).
Bake in square cake tin in moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ice with buttercream icing.
Decorate with remaining nuts.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple and instant pudding; mix well. Stir in sour cream. Add coconut, chopped walnuts, marshmallows, cherries and oranges. Stir in Cool Whip, mixing well.
Chill.

title: big sur trail mix
directions: Toast oats by preheating oven to 250° and baking 1 hour, shaking pan occasionally.
Toast nuts with oats.
Cool and mix in raisins and dates.
Store in covered container.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate sliced, prepared vegetables overnight or for several hours.

title: bob's barbecue sauce
directions: Pour into pan and bring to boil.
Pour half over chicken and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet iced tea
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and set aside to steep for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and lemonade concentrate.
Put in gallon container and add enough water to make one gallon of tea.

title: apple pie
directions: Use unbaked pie shell and fill with grated apples, raisins and pecans, if desired.
Then pour topping over the apples.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: grandmom stuart's rice ring
directions: Mix, place in a well greased tube pan.
Bake at 350°, 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before turning onto a large platter.

title: cheese beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces; brown until crisp.
Add beans and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve with cornbread.

title: pork chops in barbecue sauce
directions: Brown chops in margarine; remove.
Saute onion until browned. Add remaining ingredients and cook 20 minutes.
Pour over chops in a baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butter rolls
directions: Make dough as for biscuits.
Roll the dough out in the shape of a pie crust and about 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread butter over rolled-out dough.
Next, sprinkle sugar over butter.
Sprinkle nutmeg over sugar.
Roll up the dough like a jelly roll and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in a deep casserole which can be heated on top of the stove or in oven.
Pour water over rolls and place on medium heat on top of stove.
Take a spoon and lift each roll so that the water gets under each roll.
When it comes to a boil, place in oven and bake until lightly browned.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and make into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until brown.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, beat egg yolks with condensed milk and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 pie.

title: glaze for pork
directions: You can add a little chickory if smoke flavor is desired.

title: cherry berry on a cloud
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Butter an oblong pan (9 x 13-inches). Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Gradually beat in 1 3/4 cups sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy (15 minutes).
Spread in pan and bake 60 minutes.
Leave in oven overnight (do not open door).
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Gently fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Spread over meringue and refrigerate overnight.

title: pot poulet
directions: Cut up chicken into serving pieces.
Also cut up sausage, pepper and onions.
Brown chicken and sausage in oil with crushed garlic clove.
Be careful not to burn garlic.
Set chicken and meat aside.
Lightly saute onions, mushrooms and green pepper in same oil.
Put chicken, sausage, vegetables, tomatoes, beans and wine in a heavy casserole with a tight fitting lid.
There should be enough liquid to cover meat, etc.
Include juice from beans in can.
If more liquid is needed, add more wine.
Mix gently.
Cover tightly.
Cook at least 2 to 2 1/2 hours in a moderate oven at 350°.
Test meat for doneness, but the long, slow cooking brings out the flavors.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: quiche
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Fill pie shell with mixture and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: italian beef
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot to cook on low for 15 to 20 hours.
As the meat cooks, use a fork to break it up completely.
Serve on Kaiser rolls, hard rolls or noodles.

title: basque chicken stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven with salt and pepper. Cook chicken 2 minutes per side. Add onion and red pepper. Cook 3 minutes.
Add garlic and cook 30 seconds.
Add tomatoes, broth, potatoes and thyme.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cover. Simmer 20 minutes. Add macaroni and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Add olives.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve with crusty French bread.

title: crazy cake(chocolate)
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix all dry ingredients (flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt).
Then sift the dry ingredients into an ungreased loaf pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
With the back of a mixing spoon make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Pour melted shortening in one, vinegar in second and vanilla in third.
Pour water over the top.
Mix and blend thoroughly until batter is smooth.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
(Watch carefully, cake will appear wet on top, don't overbake.)
Cool.
Frost as desired.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Heat skillet on moderate fire (300°).
Add oil and heat thoroughly.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Drain off excess oil. Combine soy sauce, sherry, sugar and garlic.
Pour into pan with chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 25 minutes in a covered pan. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet, salt and pepper.
Drain and put in a casserole dish.
Peel and slice onions and potatoes.
Layer on meat and pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Use small party carrots or cook fresh carrots until tender. Drain and save juice.
Add pineapple and chestnuts to carrots. Use pineapple juice and mix with flour or cornstarch and sugar. Cook until thick, then pour over hot carrots, pineapple and chestnuts.
Heat well.

title: fried corn
directions: Remove husk and silk from corn; cut twice real thin.
Scrape down.
Mix corn, salt, black pepper, sugar, flour and cold water. Mix well.
Melt shortening; pour corn in skillet.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
Add oleo and continue cooking for about 20 minutes more.
Stir continually until done.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and granulated sugar.
Add eggs, beating until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt to oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: holiday soup
directions: Cook kale and spinach in chicken broth 1 hour.
Bring to a boil, then turn off heat.
Blend semolina, eggs, Romano and lemon rind and slowly stir this mixture into soup with a slotted spoon. Turn heat on to medium and cover pot 1 minute.
This will set the mixture; the soup is now ready to serve.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine salmon, oats, onion, egg, parsley, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Pan-fry on both sides until golden brown.
Serve salmon patties on buns with lettuce and tomatoes.
Serves 4.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes; cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in lemon peel and cinnamon. Continue cooking for 15 minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently.
Stir in raisins.
Remove from heat; cool slightly. Pour into prepared crust.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Cook butter, onion, garlic and meat in a heavy skillet until brown.
Break up meat with a fork.
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer the mixture until slightly thickened consistency.
Season if necessary.
Pour sauce over center of cooked spaghetti placed on a platter.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: southern peach yam bake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg in a bowl.
Cut in the margarine until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs; add the pecans and set aside.
Arrange the yams and peaches in a 1-1/2 qt. casserole or rectangular baking dish.
Sprinkle with the sugar mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and broil briefly until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oats and boiling water; set aside until cool.
Stir together yeast, lukewarm water and 1 tablespoon honey until smooth. Add to cooled oatmeal.
Then add 1/2 cup honey, soft butter, flour and salt.
Stir all together well.
Knead down in large bowl. Cover and let double in bulk (45 minutes).
Then divide into 2 kneaded loaves and let rise again (45 minutes or less) or until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.
Turn out of pans to cool.

title: philadelphia cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar in large bowl; add softened cream cheese, salt, vanilla,
egg
yolks
and
flour.
Mix all ingredients well.
On
greased
cookie sheet, drop by teaspoon or use cookie press.
Place
cherry half in the center of each cookie.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pork roast in gravy
directions: Cook pork roast until well done.
Let cool so that you can take off fat and bone.
Cut into small pieces.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice. Blend well.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: This recipe is good over ice cream.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in sour cream, add flour and soda.
Scrape bowl.
Add flavorings and beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in bundt pan at 350 degrees until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.

title: barbecued chuck roast
directions: Select a 3 to 4 pound chuck roast 2 1/2 to 3 inches thick. Place meat in shallow glass dish.
Place marinade over meat. Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours, turning meat frequently.
Remove meat from marinade.
Stir catsup into marinade.
Heat through on grill.
Brush on meat.
Place roast on grill 4 inches from medium coals.
Cook 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Turn frequently and baste every 5 to 6 minutes with hot marinade.
Serve roast to desired doneness or rare in the middle and brown on the outside.
Cook and stir garlic in oil.
Add rosemary, mustard and soy sauce.
Remove from heat and stir in vinegar and juice.

title: citrus juice tip
directions: To get the most juice from lemon or citrus fruits such as grapefruit, orange, etc., microwave on High 15 to 20 seconds per piece of fruit on floor of your microwave oven.
After allow fruit to stand 1 to 2 minutes, then roll between palms.
Fruit will give surprising amount of juice along with added flavor and fruit zest.

title: pot roast
directions: Place round roast in a little bit of oil in a large pot. Brown on all sides of the roast, adding salt and pepper to taste while browning.
Add tomato sauce and cover.
Cook on low for 5 to 8 hours.
A can of carrots and jar of onions can be added during the last hour or two.
Make gravy with the liquid, as desired.

title: jello dessert i
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients. In a separate bowl, mix Knox gelatine and water until well dissolved. Add to other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cornflakes and butter and put in a casserole dish. Toss cornflakes and butter together and put on top of casserole. Bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes. This recipe freezes well. Don't top with cornflakes until ready to bake.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 3-quart casserole dish for 20 minutes before putting on topping.
Bake at 350°.

title: gingersnaps cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and egg in a bowl.
Beat until fluffy, add molasses and beat well.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to shortening mixture.
Mix well and chill dough thoroughly.
Shape into one-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: pay day bars
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and oleo and mix good.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes (until golden brown).
Remove and sprinkle marshmallows over cake; return to oven until it puffs up.

title: overnight pea salad
directions: Cut and mix together the lettuce, cauliflower, onion and peas. Stir together the salad dressing and sugar.
Put on top. Add shredded cheese and bacon bits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix pickle, onion, celery, peppers and 1 cup cheddar cheese in bowl.
In separate mixing bowl, whip cream cheese until smooth. Add relish mixture to cream cheese, mix well.
Place mixture onto plate.
Cover with Saran Wrap and press into a ball shape.
Press remaining 1/2 cup cheddar cheese onto top of cream cheese mixture. Serve with crackers or breads.

title: zucchini skillet medley
directions: Heat oil in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add celery, onion and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, green pepper and carrots.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot or cold. May also be frozen.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time: 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn sticks
directions: Grease muffin tins. Place in oven to heat. Sift dry ingredients together. Add egg, butter and buttermilk. Pour into hot muffin tins. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fudge pudding and cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa and baking powder. Add milk and vanilla.
Mix 3/4 cup brown sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over top of first mixture.
Pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over all.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 40 minutes (adjust to your own stove).
Makes its own cake on top and sauce on bottom.

title: squash muffins(makes 12 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine egg, squash, milk and butter and stir into dry ingredients just until mixture is moistened. Spoon into greased muffin cups; bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: amanda's roasted chicken with vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, stir butter, rosemary, salt, pepper and garlic.
Rub chicken with 1/2 of butter mixture. Place chicken on rack in roasting pan.
Place vegetables around chicken and dollop remaining butter mixture over them.
Bake, basting chicken occasionally, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: italian ice cream
directions: Put 1/2 gallon ice cream in large bowl. Thaw until you can "stir" and add remaining ingredients. Refreeze. Makes 24 small servings.

title: no-beat fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a heavy saucepan and heat to boiling over medium heat.
Stir constantly and cook for 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and marshmallows; stir until mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish and let stand until set.
Cut into squares.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Melt butter; toss in onion and hamburg.
Stir until browned. Add rest of ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water until tender.
Drain, mash and drain again.
Add butter, beaten egg yolks, cream of mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into squash mixture.
Place mixture in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chewey cake
directions: Cook margarine and brown sugar together until blended. Cool. Add eggs and flour. Stir each in well. Add vanilla and pecans. Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut in squares while still warm.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo
in 9 x 12-inch pan in 400° oven.
Mix together all the other stuff. Spread on top of oleo. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain peas and corn; add pimento, pepper and onions.
Mix salt, pepper, sugar, oil and vinegar and pour over vegetables; mix well.
Will last several days in refrigerator.
Great with steak and baked potato.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop broccoli.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch dish, then add all the other ingredients to dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbling good, about 30 minutes.

title: cocktail chicken wings
directions: Lay chicken wings in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sauce and pour over wings.
Cover and marinate for 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Turn wings several times while baking.
Serve warm.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Put bread in 9 x
14-inch
pan.
Top
with
sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and
mustard; pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover with
foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, mix soup and mushrooms and
pour
on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Fill cupcake papers 1/2 full.
Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar in small bowl.
Add chocolate chips.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture on top of cake mix in papers.
Bake as directed for cupcakes on back of cake box.

title: chunky peanut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In large mixing bowl combine all ingredients except peanuts.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
By hand, stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoons 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: layered casserole
directions: Layer ingredients as listed. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: On cookie sheet or large baking dish, spread bean dip.
Add layer of avocado and lemon juice on top of beans.
Add layer of sour cream and mayo mixture (mayo, salt, pepper and taco seasoning).
Layer olives, onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, tomatoes and green chilies, bread crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan using wet hands.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: roast turkey breast with garlic and herbs
directions: Rinse the turkey with cold water.
Remove and discard all visible fat.
Pat turkey dry with paper towels.
Place the celery, carrots, onions and thyme in a roasting pan.
Place the turkey on top.
Rub the skin with the oil.
Loosen the skin and slice the garlic and herbs under it.
Rub skin with lemon juice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise, spinach (drained well) and water chestnuts (optional).
Chill well.
Serve with pumpernickel bread or sourdough bread, cut in cubes or with crackers.

title: nora's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine in crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate-n-cinnamon cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; blend well. Place in a wide-mouth jar and put lid and ring on it.

title: corn, okra and tomatoes
directions: Place cut okra in baking pan or dish.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper and celery.
Sprinkle with flour and fry on low heat until onion is limp.
Add corn and tomatoes and continue cooking on low heat for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.

title: chili de chauvanism *
directions: *Because you have to be a real man to eat this stuff!!

title: tuna and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare rice as directed on package. In large casserole dish, layer rice, tuna and half of the chips. Heat soup with water just until boiling.
Pour over tuna and rice combination.
Mix well to make sure all ingredients are moist. Cover with remaining chips.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350° or until top is golden brown.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients together in bowl.
Beat the eggs separately; add to dry mixture.
Mix until well blended; may have some lumps.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Beat together the butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture to butter mixture and mix until well blended. Add vanilla and almond extracts and mix well.
With hands, form dough, about 1/2 tablespoon at a time, into crescents or S-shapes. Place cookies 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Put on middle rack of oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes or until barely brown on edges. Remove from cookie sheet and cool 5 minutes.
With a flour sifter, sift powdered sugar over cookies.

title: 1-2-3-4 corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and season with salt and pepper.
Dot with buttered bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until center is set.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and chopped dates.
Cook on low heat for 3 to 5 minutes until melted together.
Add to hot mixture the Rice Krispies and pecans.
Let set 30 minutes to cool.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: creamy hot chocolate sauce
directions: Cook all in double boiler 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool and stir in 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Store in fridge in small stainless steel covered saucepan.
When needed to heat up, return to saucepan, then back to fridge until next time.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Spoon over 8 hot dogs.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together and then combine margarine, milk, cheese, flour and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato deluxe casserole
directions: Mix together well and pour into a 9x13 pan.
Bake 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours at 375 degrees or until potatoes are done.
(I only use 4 oz cheese).

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Pour 1/2 of margarine over stuffing mix.
Set aside. Saute onion in remaining margarine.
Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Combine all ingredients, except stuffing mix. Pour into baking dish.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel the onions.
Cut them into thick slices between 1/4 and 1/8 inch
in thickness.
Separate the slices into rings, using only the larger ones for frying.
Keep the rings that are to be fried dry.

title: low-fat pasta and sauce
directions: Fry turkey with onion and drain.
Add Ragu sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Boil noodles and mix all together.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together.
Bake chicken until almost done; pour sauce over chicken.
Takes about 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cubes in buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Scald milk with buttered sugar.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt.
Stir in warm milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread cubes.
Set baking dish in pan containing warm water up to level of pudding. Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg; cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts. Reserve 2 cups crumbs; press remainder firmly on the bottom of a greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar, add remaining ingredients and beat until frothy.
Pour into crust.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Allow to cool 5 minutes.
Pour over the topping.
Bake another 10 minutes and cool.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours before serving.
Very rich.

title: oven made caramel corn
directions: Boil butter, sugar, syrup and salt in a heavy saucepan for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add soda and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Pour over corn; stir to coat kernels.
Place in two large pans.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: red punch
directions: Use all sweetened juices or add some sugar.
Use cherry Kool-Aid to get the right color red, using a little at a time. This serves 40 to 50 people.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle and simmer at least 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: polynesian turkey
directions: Cook green pepper in butter until tender.
Drain juice from pineapple; add water to make one cup.
Stir contents of envelope of gravy mix into skillet.
Add pineapple juice, sugar, vinegar, turkey and pimento.
Heat to boiling.
Serve on cooked rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
When ready to serve, add one 2-liter bottle ginger ale.
Mix until slush.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix strawberry and 1 cup of sugar in separate bowl.
Mix flour, milk and remaining sugar in another bowl.
Melt butter in a large baking dish.
Pour flour mixture in baking dish.
Add strawberries.
(Do not stir.)
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Add ice water and put in refrigerator to begin to set.
Grind the cranberries and apple. Grate the orange zest and grind the remaining orange.
Mix fruit with sugar.
Stir into the partially set jello and return to refrigerator until firm.

title: mortal sin cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in two 8-inch round cake pans.
Remove from pans 10 minutes after removing from oven.
When cool, slice each layer in two, making four layers.
Combine sour cream, sugar and coconut and spread between the layers.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Cover with Handi-Wrap, using toothpicks to keep off cake.
Store in refrigerator 3 days before using.
When removing the toothpicks, use Cool Whip to cover holes made by toothpicks.

title: crab quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 450° for 4 minutes.
Place crab meat in pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients except Cheddar cheese and paprika in bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and paprika over top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: lush
directions: Cut in margarine,put in bottom of baking dish and bake 15 min at 350°. Cool.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer into pan: half the noodles, cottage cheese, chicken, Cheddar cheese, mushroom sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in strawberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Don't overbeat.
Pour batter into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or when tops are golden and spring back when touched.
Serve warm.

title: buckeyed balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, vanilla and confectioners sugar together.
Form balls about 1-inch.
Put on cookie sheet and put in the refrigerator.
Melt chocolate and Crisco in a double boiler. Dip each ball halfway in chocolate.
Store in a cool place.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix 3 cups milk with pudding mix; stir until it thickens. Mix in Eagle Brand milk with beater; add Cool Whip and vanilla. In a separate container, make a layer of bananas, then a layer of wafers. Pour part of mix over to cover. Make another layer of bananas and wafers and pour remaining mix to cover. Sprinkle crumbs in wafer box over the top.

title: fluffy vanilla frosting
directions: Cream butter or shortening, 1 cup of the confectioners sugar, vanilla and salt in large bowl.
Alternately add remaining confectioners sugar and milk; beat to spreading consistency. Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: wayne's chili
directions: Combine stewed tomatoes, beans and water in a large pot and bring to boil.
Add chili mix, chili powder and Spike.
Stir well and let simmer.
Brown meat in a large skillet.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and Spike.
Add 1/2 of the chopped onions to meat mixture and 1/2 of the chopped onions to the tomato mixture (small amounts at intervals).
Drain browned meat of any excess grease and add to tomato mixture and let simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: crawfish salad
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and mix with mayonnaise to desired consistency. Season to taste.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight in cooking bag. When read to cook, punch 6 holes in top of baggie.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Pour 1/2 cup Woody's barbecue sauce over brisket. Continue cooking for another hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onions, then add other ingredients and cook 2 to 3 hours.

title: caring cooks chicken & rice soup
directions: Remove cooked chicken from broth.
Debone, chop and return to broth.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes stirring 3 or 4 times.
Add condensed soups. Freezes great.
Servings 8.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk together; stirring well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into crusts and chill overnight.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion and celery until tender.
Mix mustard,
catsup and well-beaten egg.
Add to hamburger mixture and simmer.

title: deluxe cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar, butter and cinnamon in medium bowl.
Press into 10-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
Beat the cream cheese in large mixing bowl until soft and creamy. Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour cream cheese mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: mildred's salad
directions: In large bowl toss together lettuce and romaine.
Top with cheese, peas, 1/2 of bacon and all onion.
In a separate bowl, stir together mayonnaise or salad dressing, sugar and salt.
Spoon over onion.
Do not toss.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with remaining bacon and toss.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, cook the onion and ground beef in oil until brown.
Stir in all other ingredients except spaghetti. Cover and cook until mixture boils.
Break the spaghetti into pieces and add to the sauce.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Stir often.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan or large cookie sheet. Pour batter on cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if you want.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Place on a clean tea towel and roll up into a roll.
Let cool.
Unroll, fill with filling (recipe to follow).
Reroll and refrigerate.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, green pepper, onion, pickles and bacon; toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice; stir well and set aside.
Mix mayonnaise mixture into vegetable mixture.
Layer half each of vegetable mixture and cornbread in a large, glass bowl. Repeat layers.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: dieter's cheeseless cheese cake
directions: Drain pineapple; soften gelatin in pineapple juice.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Place pineapple and gelatin mixture in blender.
Blend 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until frothy.
Place in dish and chill until firm.

title: japanese fruit nut pies(2 pies)
directions: Add
sugar
to melted margarine and beat.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix	in all other ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: angel cake delight
directions: Freeze cake.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Whip well and fold in Cool Whip.
Remove cake from freezer and slice into long thin slices.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with slices of cake.
Spread the layer of cake with the cream mixture.
Repeat cake and mixture.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling. Fresh strawberries are good.

title: walsh mulled wine
directions: Put ingredients in large saucepan and heat, gently stirring well.
Don't boil.
Just let it simmer for a while until fruit and spices blend together with the wine.
Serve warm in mugs or glasses.
It will be sticky so use a napkin under the mug.
Once made mulled wine reheats well by the mug in microwave.
Keep bottled in refrigerator.
Good for body and soul on a cold winter night.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Boil green peppers for 5 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients and stuff cooled peppers, then bake 45 minutes uncovered in 350° oven.

title: scott's famous egg salad
directions: Mix and serve with crackers or on bread.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Pour mixture over carrots and marinate.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, soup mix and Parmesan cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours to overnight.
Before serving, add broccoli to mixture.
Use loaf of bread; carve out and tear into pieces.
Fill bread with dip and use bread pieces to dip with.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and cream.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Add balance of ingredients.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add milk if too thick.

title: souper rice
directions: Use any type cream soup.
In a 2-quart covered microwave dish, empty 1 can cream soup, 1 can Minute rice and 1 can milk.
Stir, cover and cook on High in microwave for 4 minutes.
Turn dish 1/4 turn and continue to cook 3 more minutes.
Stir, cover and let stand 5 minutes or until all of the milk is absorbed.

title: red rice casserole
directions: Put rice in casserole.
Cover with tomatoes. Add chopped onion, salt, pepper and sausage. Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon.
Remove and drain.
Saute onion and peppers.
Add rice and stir to coat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Place in ovenproof pan or dish, cover and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture alternately with pumpkin. Add dates and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375°
for 10 to 15 minutes.
Ice with maple flavored icing.

title: chicken breasts with summer veggies
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
In a large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat. Add chicken and cook, turning once, until browned (about 10 minutes).
Pour chicken broth over chicken. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add basil and vegetables to pan. Cover and cook for 5 minutes until vegetables are slightly tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning mix with sour cream and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Layer on a serving dish the ingredients in the order listed, starting with the sour cream and taco mixture.
Do not mix ahead of time as the dip will become soggy.

title: jamie's creamy chicken breast supreme
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer cubed chicken, mushrooms and broccoli.
In separate bowl, combine sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Spread over chicken mixture and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quick microwave fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa. Make well in center. Put can milk and butter in center of well. Microwave 2 minutes on high. Add vanilla, peanut butter and nuts. Stir and pour in buttered 8 x 8 inch dish and refrigerate.

title: slam dunk flank steak(sunset's "easy basics" cookbook)
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of the butter with the oil in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Place meat in pan and cook, uncovered, until meat is browned on both sides but still pink in center when slashed.
Transfer meat to a carving board and cover loosely to keep warm.
Over low heat, melt the remaining 3 tablespoons butter in pan drippings.
Mix in vermouth, mustard, Worcestershire and capers; stir briskly to blend.
Cut meat across the grain into thin slanting slices.
Spoon sauce over meat.
Garnish with watercress, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Soften yeast in warm water; add buttermilk.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture to form soft dough.
Turn on floured board and knead for one minute.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place in greased pan.
Let rise for one hour.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in a 1-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes until firm.

title: cream cheese potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine the water and bouillon. Add the cream cheese; cook and stir until cheese is melted. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 18 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: plum brandy
directions: Wash plums.
Prick with a fork.
Put them into a large jar. Add sugar cubes and gin.
Let brew, strain and enjoy.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Blend flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in lard and oleo until grainy.
Stir in sugar, nutmeg and currants.
Beat eggs and mix with milk.
With a fork, mix all ingredients to form a soft dough.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into rounds of desired size.
Bake on an ungreased griddle, 325° to 350° if electric.
Bake on one side until golden brown.
Turn; cook on other side.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together all the ingredients and form into walnut size balls.
Cook 15 minutes at 350° on an ungreased pan.
Can be frozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before frosting.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; pour into large bowl. Add cooked limas, corn and tomato and green onions. Make a dressing of the oil, sugar and cayenne pepper. (If you don't like hot, reduce cayenne.) Salt and pepper the spaghetti and vegetables; toss with dressing.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, then place in a casserole dish and add the remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tallerine
directions: Cook onions, pepper and garlic salt in oil for a few minutes. Add hamburger meat and brown.
Layer, into a large casserole dish: 1/2 of meat, corn, soup, tomatoes, noodles, chili powder, salt and cheese.
Repeat, using the other 1/2 of everything, having grated cheese on top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: canned apple pie mix
directions: To tell if eggs are fresh, place an egg in a pan of cold water.
If it lies on its side, it's fresh.
If it tilts, it's about 3 to 4 days old.
If the egg stands upright, it's probably at least 10 days old.
If it floats to the top, it shouldn't be used.

title: mesquite-smoked fajitas
directions: Trim skirt steak to remove membrane and bits of fat.
Rub meat with lemon pepper and place in a refrigerator dish.
Combine beer and Italian dressing and pour over meat.
Marinate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave the Cheddar and cream cheese at room temperature for 1 hour. Mix together Ranch mix, milk and mayonnaise. Mix in the cream cheese with an electric mixer, then stir in the Cheddar cheese. Put in freezer for 30 minutes, then shape into a ball. Roll in toasted pecans and serve with crackers.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Put soda and cocoa in water.
Mix everything except flour. Add flour last.
Bake in 350° oven in 9 x 13-inch pan 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Thoroughly blend powdered sugar, peanut butter, margarine or butter, vanilla and salt.
Shape into 1/2 inch balls.
Place chocolate pieces and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Heat over boiling water until chocolate and paraffin are melted (water in bottom of double boiler should not touch top pan).
Insert a wooden pick into candy ball; dip 3/4 of the ball into melted chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper until set.
Remove wooden picks and smooth over holes.
Place in small paper bonbon cups, if desired. Makes 8 dozen.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, oil and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and press with bottom of glass which has been dampened and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown.
Grease cookie sheet only first time.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and melted shortening (slightly cooled).
Amount of milk to use will depend upon thickness of pancakes desired.
Three-fourths cup of milk will give thick cake, 1 1/4 cups milk will give thin cake. Pour into flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten the dry ingredients.
After mixing ingredients, bake on hot griddle. Makes 1 to 1 1/2 dozen cakes.

title: turtle pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Press into 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: june harris' pepper steak
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 20 minutes in oil.
Pour off oil and add last 4 ingredients.
Simmer until tender.
Next, mix 3 tablespoon flour with 1/2 cup water and add to mixture along with 1 cup water.
Cook until thick.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: steamed graham pudding
directions: Mix all together and
put in a dish that holds at least 3/4 of a gallon, we prefer granite or Pyrex.
Steam slowly for 2 hours. This is good served with milk.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in saucepan; stir in milk.
Cook until thick, about 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and gradually add to mixture.
Cook about 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
In casserole dish, put layer of wafers and top with sliced bananas.
Pour about half of mixture over bananas, then another layer of wafers, bananas and rest of mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff; add the 1/4 cup sugar and beat to stiff peaks. Put on top of mixture.
Bake top just to brown.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Add all ingredients to the potatoes and whip with mixer.
Add sour cream gradually for desired consistency.

title: shrimply divine dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with remainder of ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 to 1 2/3 cups dip.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on High speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients. Spread into well-greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with finely chopped walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
While still warm put cake on brown bag sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll bag and cake together.
Cool; unroll.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Heat 1/2 can tomato soup.
Mix gelatin
to the remaining tomato soup.
Then mix both soups together.
Add
soup mixture to cheese mixture; stir and blend.
Add shrimp and chill until firm.

title: vegetable medley quiche
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with foil.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk and butter.
Do not stir.
Place in microwave dish.
Cook on High for 2 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Add vanilla; stir until blended.
Pour into foil-lined pan.
Smooth with spoon.
Freeze 10 minutes to set.
Cut 64 (1-inch) squares. Place pecan half on each.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Brown hamburg in skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serve with open faced hamburger rolls.

title: honey pumpkin bars
directions: Grease a jelly roll pan.
Beat sugar, honey, margarine, eggs and pumpkin in a large bowl.
(Batter will be slightly curdled.) Stir in remaining ingredients, except glaze and nuts.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: grilled red snapper with salsa
directions: Preparation time:
20 minutes plus 1 hour for marinating. Cooking time:
5 to 6 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: In bowl, beat cream cheese until well creamed.
Stir in pineapple, peppers, onions, seasoned salt and 1/2 cup pecans. Blend well.
Shape into two balls.
Roll into remaining pecans. Sprinkle with parsley and place a cherry on top for garnish. Wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Cream the cheese and instant pudding.
Beat in crushed pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: buddig beef cheese ball
directions: Mix and form a ball (can be divided for 2 smaller balls). Take the extra pack that is left and roll the ball or balls until covered with the remaining beef. This is great served on crackers.

title: sour cream orange cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat in eggs, sour cream and soda.
Put raisins and whole orange (peel and all) through food grinder.
Add to first mixture, including juice.
Gradually beat in flour, mixing well.
Turn batter into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Melt oleo in heavy pot and saute green pepper.
Add pimento. Blend in flour, salt and red pepper.
Add milk gradually.
Cook at slow boil 2 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Gently fold in crabmeat (drained with cartilage discarded).
Put in lightly greased ramekins or casserole dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: harvard beets
directions: In double boiler mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, cloves and vinegar.
Stir until smooth.
Cook and stir until clear.
Add beets and leave over hot water about 30 minutes.
Just before serving, heat, but do not boil.
Add butter and marmalade.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter or margarine thoroughly.
Add extract.
Gradually stir flour into creamed ingredients.
Work nuts into dough.
Chill well.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until set but not brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar immediately.
Cool on rack.
Roll in sugar again.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
5 dozen snowballs.

title: lefse
directions: Roll thin and fry on griddle until flecks of brown, then flip lefse over and bake on other side.
Lay on towel and cover. Sprinkle water on towel to keep it damp.
Refrigerate when done. Put wax paper between.

title: aunt margie's sticky wings
directions: Mix soy sauce and marmalade; put over chicken and let sit overnight.
Take chicken out of sauce and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned coconut pie
directions: Blend sugar, butter and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: vegetable sauce
directions: Cream butter, cheese and salt.
Blend in sour cream, chives and cucumbers.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
To serve, pour sauce over cooked vegetables while they are hot.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press in pan. Chill 5 minutes or can bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with other 1/4 cup sugar and the 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of the Cool Whip.
Spread over the crust.
Prepare the pudding, using the 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over the cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Spread the remaining half of the Cool Whip over the pudding.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together first.
Then add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook on low for 6 hours in crock-pot.

title: hot fudge dessert
directions: In a small saucepan, mix milk, syrup and butter or margarine. Bring to a boil (medium heat); simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Cool completely.)

title: banana daiquiri
directions: In blender, combine grapefruit juice, banana and ice.
Process until frothy.
If desired, garnish with mint or lime.
Makes 2 servings.

title: date balls
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over medium heat in double boiler for 10 to 12 minutes, until dates are melted.
Stir in Rice Krispies, vanilla and pecans while hot.
When cool, make into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 70 to 80 pieces.

title: shrimp pasta salad
directions: Prepare all ingredients and mix together.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Better prepared the day before.
Makes 8 or more servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pecans.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Divide into 2 balls; roll in pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: oat-n-crunch brownies
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare brownie mix according to package directions; spoon into prepared pan. Combine pecans, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon (if desired). Stir in butter. Stir in candy; sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: mom's pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in heated oil in large skillet.
Add pepper, onions and celery.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in molasses, soy sauce, lemon juice and seasoning.
Blend water and cornstarch.
Quickly stir into beef mixture. Cover. Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice and/or heated Chinese noodles.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.
Add a touch more lemon juice to cut sweet taste.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake, butter and 1 egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix softened cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar, then pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar after cake cools a bit.
Slice into bars.
Yummy!

title: dill carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and slice into 1/2-inch thick rounds.
Cook until tender and drain completely.
Add butter and stir until it melts.
Add dill and gently toss.
Serve hot.

title: low fat banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and bananas.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Put into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop
tomatoes	and cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt; cover with cloth.
Let stand 12 hours.
Drain liquid off.
Mix into tomato mixture,
bell pepper, onions, red pepper, hot pepper, sugar and black pepper.
Bring to a boil about 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Add whole cloves.
Pack in pint jars and seal. Very good with field peas, butter beans and meats.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti 10 minutes; drain.
Toss with butter.
Cook pepperoni in water to cover for 5 minutes; drain.
Saute onion in remaining butter until translucent.
In large casserole layer ingredients in this order:
1/2 spaghetti, 1 can tomato sauce, 1/2 Swiss cheese, 1/2 spices and salt, 1/2 onions, mushrooms and pepperoni and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with second layer. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown and bubbly.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 2-quart casserole. Cook for 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes (candy thermometer should read 260°), if not, cook longer.
Beat egg whites very stiff in a large bowl.
Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites and continue beating at high speed until candy loses gloss, about 12 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts to beaten mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well. Cut each potato in half lengthwise, then cut into wedges. Boil wedges for 5 minutes in salt water.
Drain. Spread wedges in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 more minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and cheese is melted.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Cook, stirring often, until thick.
Pour into sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Add 1/2 of cheese and pour over cooked macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: marinated mushroom medley
directions: Marinate
mushrooms,
olives, heart of palm, artichokes and onion
in
salad dressing 5 to 6 hours.
Just before serving, toss with lettuce and spinach.

title: apple cake(makes 1 cake)
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together; cut in butter. Bind together with egg yolk/milk mixture; press into bottom of 8 x 8 or 7 x 10 pan. Core and slice 3 cups apples. Arrange on pastry. Sprinkle topping on top. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown burger and onion in saucepan; add Ragu and simmer. Lightly grease large muffin pan (back side).
Separate biscuits and roll each one flat.
Place biscuits on the back of the muffin pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Remove and fill each one with the sauce mixture and then sprinkle with the cheese.
Place back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash salted potatoes.
Add the dip and cottage cheese.
Mix well and place in a buttered casserole.
Put cheese slices on top and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water in heavy saucepan until it reaches 235° on candy thermometer.
Pour half of this mixture into egg whites and mix well.
Cook remaining syrup to 250°.
Beat into egg white mixture and add vanilla and pecans.
Beat until nearly cold. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Yield 3 to 4 dozen pieces.

title: chicken tetrazzini(low-fat)
directions: About 2 hours before serving, in a large saucepot, place chickens, 1 onion, 1 tablespoon salt, pepper and water to cover. Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: italian cheese dressing
directions: With a wire whisk, beat together all ingredients. Refrigerate.
Mix before serving.
Can be made ahead.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: quick shrimp curry
directions: Mix undiluted soup, sour cream, curry powder, onion and pepper in a large saucepan until blended.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring once or twice.
Add shrimp and raisins; reduce heat to low and cook, stirring occasionally, for 8 minutes until shrimp are opaque throughout.
Serve immediately over hot rice.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat.
(Add spices and onion while cooking; I use about 2 to 3 tablespoons chili powder and about 2 tablespoons cumin powder).

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and place in casserole with onion, soup and Cheez Whiz; stir.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with onion rings and bake 10 minutes.

title: syble's country biscuits
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Cut in 1 cup Crisco into flour mixture until coarse like meal.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Take out what you need.
Rol out. Cut and bake in hot oven.
Will keep up to 7 days in refrigerator.

title: gooood chip dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add all ingredients.
