Cook in crock-pot until all cheese has melted, then dip with your favorite chips.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, stir well.
Yields 30 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together in mixing bowl and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cook for 1 hour at 250°.
Add more shredded cheese on top the last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: spicy grilled citrus chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in a bowl.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Boil marinade for 1 minute.
After the chicken has cooked for 5 minutes on grill, spoon marinade over the chicken.
Grill and baste, turning every 5 minutes for about 20 minutes.

title: crummy baked haddock
directions: Arrange fish in a buttered pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top. Mix butter with enough cracker crumbs so crumbs are moist and will stick together.
Spread crumbs generously over fish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix by hand cake mix, egg and margarine.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Pat mixture evenly over the bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top of mixture.
In a mixer, cream eggs, confectioners sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and almond extract.
Pour over top of first mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan and cut in squares.

title: chewy bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat. Add vanilla, then flour and fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured oblong dish for 30 to 40 minutes.
Keep testing with a toothpick for doneness.
Don't let it get too done because it won't be chewy.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Trim stems and finely chop figs.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: Cut the roll of paper towels in half with an electric knife or sharp knife.
Place in a container with lid (old Chubs container). Bring all ingredients to a boil, pour over towels and close lid. Cool before using.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, let stand.
Stir together hot water, Crisco, salt, sugar and eggs.
Add cold water.
Add yeast dissolved in water.
Add flour, mix well.
Place on floured board and knead.
Put in greased bowl and set in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Break off and make biscuits.
Place in greased pans.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Let rise about 2 hours. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Fill tortillas with other ingredients and wrap in paper towels.
Makes 18 to 20.
Freezes real good.
Microwave 45 seconds if thawed or 1 1/2 minutes if frozen.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak overnight the beans.
Parboil until beans begin to foam with Baking Soda.
Place Onion in bottom of pot.
Add beans and cover with hot water.
Stir in the Salt Pork, Dry Mustard, Molasses and Salt.
Mix and bake for 6 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: snicker bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions on box.
Pour half of mixture into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
This is the crust. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile, melt caramels with oleo and milk.
Pour over baked crust.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel mixture.
Spread remaining batter over top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Continue baking 10 minutes at 325°.
This freezes great.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 11-inch pan, except for crackers and butter.
Mix butter and crackers and sprinkle on top. Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and put in greased baking dish. Top with potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar together and cook until a rich brown.
Add the scalded milk and let heat until sugar is dissolved.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add cornstarch and pour milk mixture over gradually, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate at 450° for 10 minutes, then in a 320° oven, 30 minutes.
Cover with meringue using the egg whites.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat out rolls into two 9 x 13-inch baking dishes. Bake each at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown. Cool. Mix package of Hidden Valley dressing mix, cream cheese and Miracle Whip. Spread over cooled rolls. Top with layers of grated vegetables. Then top with olives, cheese and bacon bits. Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, pimentos, mayonnaise, lemon juice and almonds.
Put in greased cake pan.
Cover with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour and cinnamon; blend with egg mixture.
Fold in carrots, pineapple and nuts; place in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake 30 minutes in 2 layer pans.

title: tea cup chain punch
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add tea, cloves and cinnamon.
Brew strong.
Steep 5 minutes more than instructions call for and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill or heat.
Serve with orange slices as garnish.
Good served hot or cold.

title: ham quiche
directions: Sprinkle ham over bottom of pastry shell.
Heat cream cheese and milk over low heat, until smooth.
Remove from heat, gradually stir cream cheese mixture into beaten eggs, add salt and mustard; mix well.
Pour into pastry sell, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake 40 minutes longer, or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and lemon juice.
Stir in Sure-Jell a small amount at a time.
Beat hard by hand for 20 minutes.
Add syrup slowly, then add sugar slowly.
Let set 30 minutes.
Put in containers.
Freeze.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in margarine until they are transparent.
Mix other ingredients with onions.
Pour into casserole dish; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Brown in oven at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: onion pie
directions: Boil onions in salted water until transparent, about 15 minutes.
Reserve
a
small
amount
of
crackers
and cheese. Combine all
remaining
ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole
dish.
Top
with reserved cheese and crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to 380° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let set 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.
Top with whipped cream, slivered almonds, shaved chocolate curls or serve plain.

title: parmesan swiss potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish. In small bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and parsley; set aside. Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until mixture boils and slightly thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in Swiss cheese until melted.
Add potatoes to Swiss cheese mixture, breaking up clumps of frozen potato if necessary; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish; cover with foil.

title: apricot spice bars(makes 24 bars)
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add 1 egg, evaporated milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat until blended.
Stir in apricots, nuts and coconut.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Beat eggs, add all other ingredients.
Make night before and refrigerate.
Bake in the morning 45 minutes at 350°.

title: papa's scalloped potatoes & ham
directions: Spray a large casserole dish with cooking oil spray. Arrange a layer of sliced onions on bottom. Add a layer of potatoes on top of onions. Sprinkle potatoes & onions with salt & pepper and flour. Cut up a pat of butter to place on top of potatoes. Arrange ham slices on top of potato layer. Repeat, ending with a layer of onions. Pour milk over dish until the ingredients are almost covered. Cover and bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses in a food processor.
Stir in minced onion and Worcestershire sauce.
On a piece of wax paper, pour walnuts. Spoon cheese mixture on the top of the walnuts and roll into a ball.
Serve with crackers of any type.

title: fast vagabond stew
directions: Crumble beef into hard, plastic colander.
Set in a 4-quart simmer pot.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once. Discard fat.
Transfer beef to simmer pot.
Stir in taco seasoning.
Add beans, undrained tomatoes and corn.
Place the potatoes around the outside of stew.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spicy cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and spices.
In a large bowl, beat oleo and sugar with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in egg. Gradually add flour mixture, beating until blended. Divide dough in thirds.
Shape each into a ball. Flatten to 1-inch thick rounds. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour or until firm enough to roll.

title: turkey rice skillet
directions: Saute mushrooms, carrots, and zucchini in large skillet for three minutes.
Add tomatoes, water, basil, thyme and sausage. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand about 8 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake 350° for 45 minutes or until center is done. Take out of oven and cover with remaining spaghetti sauce. Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes. Take out of oven and sprinkle with grated parmesan. Serve with favorite pasta. Angel Hair Pasta is good.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix in bowl in order listed.
Beat 2 minutes.
Put into 2 greased 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first four ingredients in a bowl, press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next five ingredients in a bowl and pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raisin spice cake with walnuts and cherries
directions: Boil raisins 5 minutes; drain and save water.
Break 1 cup walnuts.
Cut up 1 (8 ounce) jar maraschino cherries.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add raisin water with baking soda dissolved in it.
Add flour and spices, then remaining cup of coffee.
Lastly, add raisins, nuts and cherries.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.
Use 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook the squash and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender; drain.
In a bowl, combine the condensed soup, sour cream and dressing.
Stir in melted butter.
Spread half the dressing mixture in bottom of greased baking dish.
Top with squash and onion.
Sprinkle the rest of dressing mixture on top of vegetables.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ranch chicken(one dish meal)
directions: Roll chicken in mixture of 1 cup flour, the salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt the butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken, skin side down.
Baste occasionally.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for about 40 to 50 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Add the drained peaches; bake 15 minutes longer.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in 2 cups boiling water until tender.
Brown beef and onion.
Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Dot with butter and cover with bread or cracker crumbs. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix everything together except margarine.
Shape into six patties.
Melt margarine in frypan.
Over medium heat, brown patties on both sides.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix.
Layer bean dip, sour cream mixture, avocado dip, olives, tomatoes and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Make a day ahead.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Use strong nacho chips for dipping.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Turn on oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in the oven.
Then sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Press crust down. Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with rest of ingredients. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until coconut is browned.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: microwave toffee squares
directions: Microwave 1 tablespoon oleo in 8 x 8-inch dish on High until melted.
Spread over bottom and 1/4-inch up sides.
Line bottom with graham cracker squares.
In small bowl, combine 1/2 cup oleo and brown sugar.
Microwave on High 1 minute.
Beat until smooth and micro 2 more minutes on High.
Pour evenly over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Micro at full power 1 1/2 to 3 minutes or until mixture boils 1 minute.
Rotate 1/4 turn every 30 seconds. Cool 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
When soft, spread to frost bars.
Allow to cool.
Cut in 1/4's.
Remove 1/4's and cut in small pieces.
For crisp toffee, store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla; blend until creamy.
Blend in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts. Melt margarine. Add cream cheese.
Beat in sugar with mixer.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake mix.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all but tomato sauce together.
Put loaf in pan.
Pour 1 (8 ounce) can Hunt's tomato sauce over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches (cookies)
directions: Combine butterscotch and peanut butter.
Heat until melted and smooth.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Press 1/2-inch greased 9 x 12 pan.
Chill.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and use for cooking pudding according to directions.
Use juice and not milk.
When cool, add to fruit.

title: slice and bake chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cut 4 14x12-inch pieces of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter, sugar and brown sugar together.
Beat in vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
In seperate bowl combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Gradually stir flour mixture into creamed mixture until well blended.
Add in 2 cups semi sweet chocolate chips and nuts.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Wrap each in waxed paper and cover in air tight container or foil.
Label with date.
Can be frozen up to 6 months. To bake:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut frozen dough into 1-inch thick slices.
Cut each slice into 4 equal pieces.
Arrange on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 min. until lightly brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: fruit 'n' pudding crisp
directions: Combine fruit, reserved 1 tablespoon dry pudding mix, 1/4 cup brown sugar and reserved 1/4 cup fruit syrup in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole or 8-inch square baking pan.
Set aside. Combine flour, oats, nuts, sugar, salt, cinnamon, pudding mix and butter in a large mixing bowl until well blended and crumbly. Sprinkle over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until deep golden brown and bubbly.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: snow painting
directions: Fill bottles with colored water.
On a snowy day, let child take bottle outside and paint their own pictures in the snow.

title: cheesy potato slices
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup, paprika, pepper, sour cream and cheese.
In a buttered casserole (2-quart oblong), arrange potatoes in overlapping rows.
Pour soup and cheese mixture over top.
Cover and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes, or until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: whole wheat quick bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, blend very well.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
Put in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 F for 50-60 minutes.
Check for browning.
This bread may need to be covered with foil the last 15 minutes to prevent over-browning.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Pour into a saucepan and heat (do not boil) the milk, Grape-Nuts and butter.
Prepare in a separate dish the eggs, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour the ingredients into the saucepan with the milk.
Mix all together, then pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on the top (optional).
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour, or until a knife comes out clean from the center.

title: emma's tea
directions: Heat tea bags in 2 cups hot water.
Mix sugar in hot tea and add lemonade.
Add 42 ounces water for a total 64 ounces liquid.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add oats and beat again.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Can be made in drop cookies or add extra flour and make rolls which can be frozen, then sliced.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix the milk and pudding until it starts to thicken.
Add the Cool Whip, sour cream and pineapple.
Stir all ingredients well and layer with vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: corn bread
directions: Pour boiling water over cornmeal; let stand until cool.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light, then add to cornmeal.
Add milk, flour and melted butter.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Pour into a shallow, well greased pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: a man's casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute onion in butter.
Set aside.
In same skillet, cook meat in oil.
Add salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook 10 minutes and add onions.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in a 2-quart baking dish. Top with parsley and 2 cups crushed potato chips. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: zesty salt-free seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in airtight container.

title: turkey a la king
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper; cook over low heat until bubbling.
Remove from heat and stir in broth and cream or milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in cut up turkey, mushrooms and green pepper. Just before serving, add sherry or sake.
Serve over rice, noodles, toasted bread, etc.
Serves 6.

title: elizabeth garner's slaw
directions: In large container, layer cabbage, pepper and onion.
Sprinkle sugar over this (do not mix).
Bring other ingredients to a boil. Pour over cabbage (do not mix).
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, mix well.
Will keep three weeks in refrigerator.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Lightly grease 10 x 1 1/2 inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onions in skillet until brown.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate. Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth. (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer.)
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 35 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes longer.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: five star fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to chocolate mixture.
Pour batter into 3 (8-inch) layer pans, which have been greased and lined with wax paper. Bake in moderate oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Mix
crumbs
and
Parmesan
cheese.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise;
coat
with crumbs. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in
13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Rinse frozen peas and carrots in cold water to separate; drain.
Heat margarine in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat until melted.
Stir in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Roll two-thirds of the pastry into 13-inch square.
Ease into ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Pour chicken mixture into pastry-lined pan.
Roll remaining pastry into 11-inch square.
Place square over filling.
Turn edges under and flute.
(You can cut designs with cookie cutters from remaining pastry and place on top of crust!)
Bake about 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet and salty candy
directions: Break up the pretzels into small pieces.
Mix equal amounts of peanuts and pretzels in bowl, and pour the melted chocolate over them.
Stir well.
Spoon onto waxed paper in heaping teaspoonfuls.
Let cool.
Store in a container with a tight-fitting lid.

title: carrie's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Stir until mixed.
Add next 3 ingredients to yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups flour.
This may be mixed by hand or mixer.
Add 2 eggs.
Add up to 3 more cups of flour to mixture.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Roll the dough out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Fold over each in half and brush with melted butter.
Let rise again 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour this mixture over the corn flakes.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: garden stir-fry
directions: Prepare the vegetables and drain them on paper towel to remove excess moisture.
Heat the olive oil and garlic in a wok or deep skillet just until the garlic is golden. Add the vegetables all at once, turning frequently, until tender but not soft, about 5 minutes.
Add the red wine vinegar, oregano and cilantro.
Toss quickly.
Remove from the skillet and serve at once.
May be served as a side dish or over pasta or rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Fry to brown meat pieces in small amount of oil.
Add water to cover 2 to 3 inches over meat.
Add a small amount of all spices; stir and cover.
Cook 2 hours.
Thicken if necessary.
Serve over noodles.
If desired, you may add sour cream at end of cooking.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans or a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in layer pans, 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Mix together.
Keep warm in crock-pot while dipping. Refrigerate.

title: cheese appetizer balls
directions: Cream butter and blend in cheese.
Add flour and seasonings and mix well.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
If dough is too sticky to handle, chill for several hours.
Place balls on greased cookie sheet, about 1 inch apart and wrap in foil.
Freeze.
Thaw and bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chunky cheese macaroni
directions: Cook the elbow macaroni in the boiling salted water in a large kettle until tender (13 minutes).
Drain.

title: lime delight
directions: Mix jello as directed for quick set.
Chill until partially firm.
Add rest of ingredients and chill until firm.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Combine peaches, undrained pineapple, strawberries, bananas and pudding in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: lo-cal vegetable stew
directions: Cook ground turkey in microwave until done.
Drain off fat. Combine all ingredients in large pan.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Add water to get desired consistency.
Add salt or salt substitute and/or pepper or Mrs. Dash, if desired.

title: no cook coconut pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat pudding mixes, milk and coconut extract on low speed until combined.
Beat on high for 2 minutes. Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with coconut that has been toasted.
Chill until serving time. Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: streusel filled coffee cake
directions: Sift flour once before measuring, then sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or rub with fingers until blended and is like fine cornmeal.
Mix in egg, vanilla and milk.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 13 pan.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni by directions.
Saute mushrooms and onion. Add to rice, stirring in soups, cooked broccoli, cooked chopped chicken, pepper, salt and garlic.
Stir together in casserole dish, mixing in 1/2 package sliced Velveeta.
Top with remaining Velveeta.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dressing for slaw
directions: Thoroughly blend ingredients and pour on 16 ounces of shredded slaw.

title: spreadable cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, cheese spread, margarine, onion powder and garlic powder.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: cheddar pinwheels
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 2 rolls 1 inch in diameter.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
When ready to use, slice the rolls into 1/8-inch rounds.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: cream sherbet punch
directions: In 6 to 6 1/2-cup ring mold, arrange thin citrus slices and maraschino cherries or strawberries in an attractive design.
Pour water into mold to partially cover fruit.
Freeze.

title: delicious rump roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and garlic salt and place in roasting pan. Chip up oleo over roast. Pour Worcestershire sauce over roast (use lots). Cook for 1 to 2 hours, depending on size of roast. Add onion, celery and potatoes and cook until done.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cranberries over the bottom of the plate and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and nuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs well.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Add flour and melted butter or shortening to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Pour batter over top of cranberries. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: chili chip dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes; mix with chili.
Put in microwave dish; microwave on High, stirring once in a while, until cheese is melted and dip is bubbly.
Serve hot with corn chips.
(Can be heated on stove top, if desired.)

title: chicken and fusilli
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In large frypan over medium heat, melt margarine.
Cook chicken until browned on all sides.
Stir in sauce and sherry and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover pan and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is done, basting occasionally with sauce.
Cook fusilli; drain.
Place on ovenproof platter.
Arrange chicken on fusilli.
Spoon sauce over all.
Place cheese slices over chicken.
Broil 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: saltwater taffy
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Place over low heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Wash down crystals.
Insert thermometer and boil, without stirring, to very firm ball, 256°. Remove from heat and add salt.
Pour on slightly oiled platter or marble and let stand only until cool enough to handle. Add vanilla and pull until light colored, starting as soon as possible. Finish in a rope 3/4-inch in diameter.
With a scissors, cut in 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in wax paper.
Use lots of butter on your hands while pulling.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Add chocolate chips.
Set mix aside.
Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt and cocoa. Add to dry ingredients the water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Put this mixture into cupcake holders. Then put 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture in each cupcake.
Bake at 350°.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
In a saucepan, heat the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Marinate for at least 6 to 8 hours.
Add other seasonings to taste (garlic powder, mixed herbs, etc.).

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine seasoning mix ingredients in small bowl and set aside. Place the vegetable oil, gizzards and pork in a large skillet over high heat.
Let cook until meat is thoroughly brown, stirring occasionally.
(5-7 minutes) Stir in the seasoning mix then add the onions, celery, garlic and bell peppers.
Scrape pan bottom well. Add the butter and heat until melted.
Reduce heat to medium and cook about 8 minutes, stirring constantly and scraping bottom of skillet well.
Add the broth and cook until any of the mixture that may be stuck come loose.
Cook over high heat for about 8 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in the chicken livers and cook 2 minutes.
Add the rice, cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and leave covered for 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Boil ingredients; add 1 cup mayonnaise and 1/2 cup mustard. Mix with blender or mixer.

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan saute onions and butter until tender. Stir in gravy, milk and broccoli.
Heat slowly, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat well with a heavy-duty mixer.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt, 1/2 cup sugar and cocoa powder.
Using a whisk, combine thoroughly.
Cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
Add ground chuck and mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
In a large skillet, brown meatballs in oil; drain.
Combine tomato sauce, water, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: Dip chicken into egg; coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides and no longer pink; keep warm.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix
Cool Whip, condensed milk, pineapple, lemon juice, pecans and
sugar	together; pour into pie shells and place in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken;
skin, debone and cut up in pieces.
Cook stuffing according to box.
Heat gravy.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put enough gravy to just cover bottom.
Put dressing on top and chicken pieces on top of dressing.
Cover with gravy.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Put into a greased baking dish or shallow casserole. Top with crushed chips and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until heated thoroughly.

title: turkey dressing pie
directions: Combine dressing and butter. Mix well. press on bottom and sides of PAM coated 9 inch pie pan or quiche plate. Bake at 400 degrees for 5 - 7 minutes. Cool.

title: pepper chicken-liberian style
directions: Skin chicken parts and steam for 15 minutes.
Mix flour, seasoned salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Dip chicken parts into batter and fry until golden brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening. Add sugar gradually and mix well.
Beat egg into mixture. Add applesauce.
Add dry ingredients. Add nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashion cream pie
directions: Work together until crumbly.
Put in pie shell.
Add whipping cream.
Add evaporated milk until pie shell is full.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Stir and bake for 15 minutes more at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together and form into loaf.
Top with 3/4 cup catsup, dry mustard and brown sugar.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Roll out and cut in cookie shapes.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: can can chicken
directions: Mix all together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until rice absorbs all liquid.

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Christmas Eve:
Place bread crumbs in a large, rectangular casserole (9 x 13-inch or larger).
Sprinkle cheese evenly over bread crumbs.
Brown and drain sausage; spread on top of cheese. Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups of milk and mustard.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops and brown on both sides; set aside.
Peel potatoes and slice round; put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Season to taste.
Mix can cream of mushroom soup with water and pour over potatoes; put sliced onion over this.
Top with browned pork chops.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peananzo
directions: Blend
the garbanzo beans, garbanzo juice, lemon juice, tomato paste
and
onion powder together.
Add chopped olives and peanut butter.
Stir into the blended mixture.
Serve as a dip or on crackers.
Add salsa if you like a Mexican flavor.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook
meat;
mix flour with 1/2 cup of juice from tomatoes. Stir
into	meat
and
add tomatoes, onions and spices. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and layer with meat sauce and Velveeta cheese slices.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Put all ingredients in pan.
When steak is brown on each side, cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be eaten over rice, noodles or just as sandwiches.

title: herbed mayonnaise
directions: Put all ingredients, except mayonnaise, in a small saucepan and cover with boiling water.
Cook 1 minute.
Drain and rinse under cold running water.
Finely chop the mixture, or process quickly in a food processor.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: crunchy party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
In a very large bowl combine pretzels, noodles, cereal, peanuts and raisins.
In medium bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over pretzel mixture; stir until well coated.
Spread evenly on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool completely in pan.
Stir in chocolate pieces (M&M's).
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
about 12 cups snack mix.

title: mustard dipping sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until smooth.
Cover and chill 1 hour or more.
Serve with shrimp, vegetables or grilled chicken kabobs.
Also good with grilled kielbasi slices.

title: pineapple inside-out cake
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Cream until fluffy. Combine flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture. Beat well.
Stir in pineapple, vanilla and pecans.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a full boil, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add butter; continue cooking, stirring occasionally until candy thermometer reaches 280° or small amount of mixture dropped into ice water forms a pliable strand, 80 to 90 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until thermometer reaches 305° or small amount of mixture dropped into ice water forms a brittle thread, 12 to 14 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Line buttered dish with crescent rolls.
Press them out firmly until they cover bottom of pan.
Put sausage first, then cheese.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over this.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then cut into pieces.

title: hot chocolate mix with powdered milk
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Store mixture in an airtight container.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Drain 1 box of strawberries and reserve juice.
Set aside. Cook cake according to directions on box.
Let cool, then poke several holes in top of cake.
Spread strawberries evenly over cake.
In microwave, melt margarine, then beat in confectioners sugar.
Stir in enough strawberry juice to make icing easy to be dropped by spoonfuls.
Pour any remaining juice over cake, then top with icing.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lemon bread
directions: Put in 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice krispies crunchies
directions: Mix cheese and oleo.
Add other ingredients; mix.
Mold into marble size balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: potato and broccoli frittata
directions: In large skillet, cook potato slices, uncovered, in hot oil for 5 minutes or until just tender, turning occasionally.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add thawed broccoli; reduce heat and cook, covered, for 5 minutes more.
Beat together eggs, cheese, water, basil, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables in skillet.
Cook over medium-low heat for 5 to 6 minutes.
As eggs set, run a spatula around the edge of the skillet, lifting egg mixture to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
Continue cooking and lifting edge until mixture is almost set.
(The surface will be moist.) Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 3 to 4 minutes or until top is set.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cut into wedges; serve from the skillet.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with nonstick cooking spray. Spread a 1/4 cup of sauce on the bottom. Boil the lasagna noodles for 15 minutes. Rinse and drain. Boil and drain the spinach. Mix the Ricotta cheese, eggs, spinach, dash of pepper, salt and parsley flakes. The noodles should be flattened out after they are drained on foil. Put a layer of noodles on the bottom of the glass dish and spread with the Ricotta mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese. Next, do another layer of noodles, sauce, Ricotta, Parmesan and Mozzarella. Depending on how many noodles you have, keep layering until done with the Ricotta mixture. On the top layer, there should be noodles, sauce, Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°. Take out of oven and cool on rack for 10 minutes before serving. Enjoy!

title: taco bake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Layer tortilla shells on bottom. Cook hamburger and drain.
Mix with stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Spread over tortilla shells.
Top with cheese.
Layer as often as you can.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
If you have
a larger pan, double ingredients.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; press into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine last ingredients; pour over crust.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; cool.
Cut into squares.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Slice apples thin and place into pan, covering entire area.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Blend remaining ingredients in bowl with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Spread mixture over apples.
Place pan on bottom rack of oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes until apples are soft and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: el dorado beef
directions: Fry hamburger, adding the next 6 ingredients after it is browned.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine and set aside the cottage cheese, sour cream and chopped chilies.
Grate cheese. Crush slightly the Doritos.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake 36 minutes longer.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruits.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add concentrate and stir until thickened.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in whipped topping and fold in fruit.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Put first five ingredients: sugar, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in center and add eggs, oil, nuts, vanilla and drained pineapple and bananas.
Stir together but do not beat.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. This will make 1 large loaf and 2 small or 2 large loaves.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave anytime broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Conventional:
Combine soup and milk over medium heat until hot and bubbling, stirring often.

title: daddy's boiled custard
directions: Cook egg yolks, milk and sugar in a double boiler or heavy pan about an hour or until it gets a little thick and changes color. Take off burner and set aside.

title: magic biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Put in oiled bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
You don't have to wait for rising.
Bake in desired manner at 400° to 450° for 10 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Slice apples in thin small pieces.
Roll out each biscuit thin; place some apples in each biscuit.
Fold the biscuit up over the apples.
In a pot, bring to a boil the 7-Up, sugar and cinnamon.
Place biscuits in a baking dish or pan.
Pour cinnamon mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Marinate the vegetables in the marinade.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain and serve. Keeps 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: sush puppy corn bread
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix only enough to dampen dry ingredients and make stiff mixture. Heat the grease very hot and turn down real low and drop by spoonful in hot grease and fry.

title: salmon pie
directions: Cook potatoes with onion and seasonings.
Take reserved salmon juice
and
onion and slowly saute in 2 tablespoons of butter for 10 minutes.
Mash potatoes and onions with salmon, juice
and egg.
Add cracker crumbs and season to taste.
Make pie crust for 1 pie (2 crusts).
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350°
for
45 minutes
until brown.
Can be served with white sauce with chopped hard-boiled egg or peas.

title: the chocolate fallen bundt cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream, Kahlua and eggs.
Add cake mix and pudding mix.
Fold in chocolate chips. Put mixture in "Joy" sprayed Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes before inverting.

title: apple raisin nut cake
directions: In large bowl, mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and mayonnaise.
Beat with electric mixer at low speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently until well blended. Batter will be thick.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with wooden spoon.
Spoon in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes (until wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes clean).

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour hot water over oleo, salt and sugar.
Stir to dissolve. Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in cup of cool water and add to mixture. Stir in beaten eggs.
Add flour gradually.
You may not use all of the flour or you may need more.
Dough should be sticky.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll out and shape.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 450 until brown.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, evaporated milk and vanilla. Mix and pour into freezer.
Fill to fill line with regular milk. Freeze.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix altogether; put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon if you like that flavor.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°. Serves 6.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add drained pineapple chunks and mix until covered.
Mix the cracker crumbs and melted margarine. Spread over pineapple mixture.
Sprinkle 3 to 4 tablespoons of pineapple juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Grated cheese may be added if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash, cook onions and squash in water until tender. Drain.
Add cracker crumbs and butter and almost all of the cheese. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Beat eggs slightly, add cream and mix into squash.
Pour into buttered casserole dish with remaining cheese on top.

title: giselle's cauliflower and broccoli toss
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli in bite-sized pieces; add chopped green onions.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over veggies. Cover; chill overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain and rinse with cold water. Drain olives and chop up into quarter sizes.
Add to mayonnaise, cayenne pepper and mustard.
Stir in cooked pasta until completely coated.
Refrigerate.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Take rolls as whole unit out of pan.
Slice horizontally with bread knife and set aside top layer.
Put bottom layer back in pan. Place ham and cheese on bottom.
How much you use is optional.
I usually cover with cheese and build up ham on that.
Melt butter, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce together. Place top of rolls back on pan and cover with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not cover.
You'll need to cut apart the rolls.
It's easier before you bake them.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Mix well. Bake at 425° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lucy's easy salad
directions: Make pudding by shaker method using milk.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add fruit cocktail, mix in pudding.
Decorate top with cherries and mandarin oranges.

title: mardi gras rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat, but do not boil. Serves 6.

title: sylvia-edgar farley  punch
directions: Boil sugar and 10 cups water 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Pour 6 quarts boiling water on green tea grounds.
Steep 5 minutes. Strain through cloth.
Cool.
Mix juices; add tea and sugar syrup. Lastly, add ginger ale and ice cubes.

title: apple brown betty(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples with cinnamon, nutmeg, brown sugar and raisins.
Drizzle honey over top of mixture and mix in.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs with 1/4 cup melted butter and walnut pieces.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the mixture over bottom of 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of apple mixture, then pour 1/2 of apple cider over that.
Layer in additional 1/3 of crumbs, remaining 1/2 of apple mixture.
Top with rest of cider and last of crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter. Cover with foil.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then drain.
Mix soups and enchilada sauce in a bowl; set aside.
Add refried beans to hamburger, and also 1 cup cheese.
Heat until mixed well.
Put scoop of meat mixture on tortilla and roll.
Place tortillas in baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over shells and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook until done.
Add chunky chicken mushroom soup and 1/2 can milk.

title: easy scampi
directions: Saut onion and parsley in butter until onion is tender. Reduce heat to low; add shrimp. Cook, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes. Remove shrimp with slotted spoon. Spoon into serving dish; keep warm. Add remaining ingredients to butter mixture; simmer 2 minutes.
Pour butter mixture over shrimp. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat in large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix together to make crumbs.
Place half of crumb mixture in long cake pan and pour cherry pie filling over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil water and dissolve bouillon cubes.
Add vegetables and potatoes.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Separate pan.
Mix soup, milk and, after heated, add cubed cheese.
Pour into vegetables.
Cook about 1/2 hour more.

title: glazed apple rings
directions: Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until melted.
Fry several apple rings at a time, turning once, until golden brown.
(Add more margarine if necessary.)
Return all apple rings to skillet.
Mix wine, lemon juice, ginger and cinnamon; pour over apples.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and cook over medium heat just until apples are tender and glazed, about 5 minutes.
Serve warm and if desired, with whipped topping.
Makes 4 servings

title: chewy chocolate macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, stir together coconut and cocoa; stir in condensed milk and vanilla until well blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Press cherry half into center of each cookie.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until almost set.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: brown rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in glass baking dish. Add soups.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: banana slush (frozen punch)
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add juices and mashed bananas.
Mix well.
Freeze at least overnight or until needed.
Remove from freezer 1 hour prior to serving.
Cut up in punch bowl and add 7-Up or ginger ale.
Serves approximately 50.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Place in greased casserole pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken macaroni bake
directions: Drain the cooked macaroni and combine with chicken, cheese, soup, milk, mushrooms, pimento and mustard.
Pour into greased with Pam casserole.
Spread mayonnaise over all.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and spread on top.
Crushed potato chips may be used instead of bread crumbs, if so desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: In casserole or roast pan, place chicken.
Cover with rice, then cream soup and dry soup.
Sprinkle water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4. If it seems too dry, add more water.

title: gary's scottish rumbledthumps
directions: Slice the potatoes thickly and boil in a little salted water. Once cooked, drain and mash.
Slice the cabbage and boil gently in salted water.
Do not over cook.
Melt the butter in a heavy bottomed pan and cook the onions.
Once soft add the cooked potatoes and cabbage.
Add a little milk, season to taste and beat together.
Place mixture in an oven safe dish and cover with grated cheddar cheese.
Place under the broiler to brown.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish lightly with cooking spray. Slice bread into 1 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place bread tightly together in one layer in baking dish.
Place eggs in bowl and beat lightly.
Add milk, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla and mix with whisk. Pour half of liquid over bread.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Cut into rings.
Place apple pieces on top of bread to cover.
Pour remaining egg mixture over apples.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Can serve with syrup.
Yields 12 servings.

title: butterscotch nut cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine until light.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and vinegar to evaporated milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoons 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven 350° about 15 minutes or until delicately brown and firm to touch.
Cool.
Frost with golden glow frosting.
Top each cookie with a walnut.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Mix Bismix and water together; beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and butter.
Mix well; pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar; refrigerate overnight.

title: imperial crab
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Thin some mayonnaise with a little milk. Grease shells and add crab mixture.
Put mayonnaise mixture on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° until top is brown (about 15 minutes).

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients into prepared 9 x 13-inch baking dish (greased and floured).
Make 3 wells in mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients with 2 cups of water.
Pour over sifted ingredients.
Stir with fork.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: short-cut white sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread evenly in ice cube tray and freeze.

title: bro. jim's fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts and fruit and dredge in half the flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each. Sift remainder of the flour with other dry ingredients.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately to cake batter.
Add nuts and fruits and mix thoroughly.
Cook in oven at 275° for approximately 4 hours.

title: bubble mix
directions: Put in a container and shake well.
Allow to settle 4 hours before using for best results.
Use a bubble wand and enjoy blowing bubbles.
For children of all ages.

title: microwave pecans
directions: Combine orange juice, sugar and pecans.
Cook in microwave on High power for 5 minutes.
Stir in butter until it melts.
Cook on High for an additional 5 minutes.
Pour out onto greased cookie sheet to cool.
Spread thinly on cookie sheet so you can break apart when cool.

title: italian peanut cream pie
directions: In food processor, chop peanuts; place aside.
In food processor, chop peanut butter chips.
Heat water in microwave oven.
Dissolve sugar and salt in water.
Start food processor and while chips are whirling around, pour in hot mixture until chips are dissolved.
Slowly at reduced speed, whirl in egg until well blended.
Cool slightly.
Pour into mixing bowl and fold in topping until well blended (no lumps).
Sprinkle 1/2 of peanuts over bottom of crust.
Spoon in cream filling.
Garnish with remaining peanuts.
Chill until firm.

title: italian sausage and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine ingredients in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cook for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour the drained pineapple juice over the sliced bananas and let stand while you mix the rest of the ingredients.
Drain bananas and add last.
Refrigerate.
Makes a large bowl of salad.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: *All should be room temperature.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and meal with a fork in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Beat with a mixer until smooth.
Pour in unbaked crust. Bake at
350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grandma coyne's fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Beat with electric mixer until thoroughly blended.
Place over rapidly boiling water (bottom of double boiler) and continue beating until frosting stands in soft peaks.
Add vanilla.
A wonderful frosting for your favorite chocolate cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press into loaf pan or form loaf with meat; top with catsup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Place onto serving platter.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate peanut candy
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients, then stir in peanuts.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper.
Toll House or Nestle morsels are good.

title: hot pot
directions: Crumble raw hamburger in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of sliced potatoes.
Add a layer of raw onion rings and salt and pepper.
Keep layering to top, ending with hamburger.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken, debone and chunk.
Add Veg-All and soup.
Mix well.
Pour in regular pie crust.
Top with another pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie crust is done.

title: ann's smoked amberjack fish spread
directions: Skin amberjack and flake in bowl.
Add next 7 ingredients and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill for 6 hours.
Serve with crackers and capers.

title: the waistwatcher
directions: Combine tuna, cabbage, olives, dressing, Tabasco and paprika. Chill mixture and spread on bread.
Serve open-faced or top with another slice of bread.
If desired, garnish with alfalfa sprouts, cucumber slices, tomato, carrot curls, etc.

title: mudgie's coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until brown on top at 350° to 375°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix bell pepper, onion, celery and tuna in a large casserole. Heat soup, milk and the butter to melt.

title: chocolate mudpie cookies
directions: Put nuts in a skillet over medium heat.
Toast until fragrant, about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Transfer to a cutting surface.
When cool enough to handle, chop coarsely and set aside. In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt, whisking to blend.
Set aside.
In top of a double boiler over simmering water, combine 1/2 of chocolate with butter.
Stir gently until melted.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool slightly.
In bowl of an electric mixer, combine sugar and eggs, beat at high speed until thick and pale yellow, about 5 minutes.
Lower speed to medium.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla, blending well.
On low speed, add flour mixture and beat just until incorporated.
Stir in nuts and remaining chocolate.
Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm enough to handle, about 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
Using a 1/4 cup ice cream scoop or a large tablespoon, drop portions of dough about 3 inches apart on sheets.
Press down with fingers to form rounds about 1/2 inch thick.
Transfer 1 baking sheet at a time to center oven rack and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are set, but still a little soft in center.
Cool sheet on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes.
Using a wide spatula, transfer cookies to a wire rack and cool completely. Makes about 1 dozen.

title: squash relish
directions: Soak the first 3 ingredients overnight. Rinse and drain good. Add the remaining ingredients. Cook 20 minutes and seal in jars.

title: keebler cracker cookies
directions: Layer a jelly roll pan with crackers.
Mix together on stove, sugar, brown sugar, margarine and milk.
Melt, then add 2 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Boil 6 to 7 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and pour remaining ingredients over them.
Cool in refrigerator one hour.
Melt together peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over top and refrigerate.
When chocolate is set, cut into squares.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for
50 to 60 minutes.

title: chilled, dilled cucumber soup
directions: Peel, seed and chop cucumbers.
Saute vegetables in butter. Process or blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in broth and milk.
Chill.
Serve garnished with dill.

title: blueberry cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shells. Top with blueberries.
Chill.

title: cold chicken rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve well chilled.

title: low-fat fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick coating and set aside.
Combine all ingredients, except flour, in a bowl and beat to blend with electric mixer on low. Stir in flour and spoon into pan.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired. Bake for 30 minutes or until top edges, about 2-inches from the center, spring back when touched with tip of finger.
Cool brownies in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Yields 36 brownies.

title: slush
directions: Make a strong tea from the tea bags and 2 cups water.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Serve partially frozen.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease 12 (3-inch) or 24 (2-inch) muffin pans.	Measure flour, sugar, pecans, oats, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into large bowl and mix well.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add extracts.
Measure 1 tablespoon of the flour and add the baking soda.
Mix and set aside.
Add last.

title: jalapeno chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Blend spinach that has been cooked and drained well.
Add jalapenos, sour cream, soup and onion tops.
In a large Pyrex pan, alternate layers of Doritos, sauteed mixture and cheese; top layer to be cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Boil for 8 minutes the green tomatoes and sugar. Add the jello. Boil 2 minutes more.
Put in jars and put in the freezer. Makes 5 to 6 cups.

title: cajun catfish fingers
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal and spices in a large bowl or bag.
Drop in fish.
Coat both sides.
Deep fry until fish floats.
Eat like popcorn or chips.
Use Open Pit for dip.
Class A good feast eating.

title: 6 layer dinner(from idaho cattlemen's association)
directions: Peel and slice enough potatoes to cover bottom of greased Dutch oven.
Pour raw rice over potatoes.
Pour drained ground beef over rice.
Add layer of onions, then peppers.
Pour tomatoes with juice over all.
Season with salt as desired.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Test rice for doneness.

title: chili con carne(method:  one pot)
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Brown hamburger with green pepper and onion.
Break up tomatoes with a fork; add to meat mixture.
Heat until boiling.
Add kidney beans and chili powder; heat through (about 5 minutes).

title: easy cobbler
directions: Using 8 x 8-inch dish or loaf pan melt margarine, being careful not to burn it.
Add fruit and juice. Combine sugar, milk and flour; pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Spread small amount of bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover with layer of wafers.
Top with bananas.
Pour about 1/3 of custard over bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers, ending with custard.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread over top of pudding, covering all of pudding top.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pickled eggplant
directions: Scrub eggplant and slice into 1/2-inch slices (or less).
Salt both sides of each slice and stack together.
Let sit overnight. Next morning, squeeze out all the juice you can.
In a kettle bring 1/2 vinegar and 1/2 water to a boil.
Add eggplant making sure they are covered with water.
Make sure liquid keeps boiling. Test eggplant with a fork as you would potatoes.
When soft, lay out open on a cloth to cool.
Do not overlap.
When cold, start packing.
Layer oil, garlic, hot pepper, then eggplant in jar. Continue to layer keeping enough oil to cover eggplant.
I use either Wesson or Mazola oil.
Good in sandwiches.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise. Spread over vegetables.
Mix margarine with cracker crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Add sugar, Crisco and milk. Mix well and add 5 eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring; beat well.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300° in preheated oven.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and celery in the boiling water, covered, until very tender.
Meanwhile melt the butter in top of double boiler.
Add flour; stir until smooth, then add seasonings and milk.
Cook while stirring until smooth and thickened, then rub the potato mixture, liquid and all, through a sieve.
You should have 3 cups puree.
Add to sauce with parsley.
Heat and serve.
Serves 6.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, sour cream, milk, onion, salt and pepper in an ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with margarine or butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine garlic, soy sauce and ginger.
Add to beef, toss over and marinate.
Heat oil in pan and add beef on high heat until browned.
Simmer until tender.
Turn up heat and add vegetables, cook
until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water. Pour over mixture.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomato wedges and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Pan-fry the onions in small amount of oil until clear.
(This makes them easier to digest.)

title: broccoli-mushroom lasagna
directions: Spread about 1/2 cup cream of mushroom soup in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer noodles seasoned with pepper, broccoli, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, remaining cream of mushroom soup and Parmesan three times.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before cutting into servings. Yields 6 servings.

title: billy goats(little date cakes)
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs; beat well, then mix with sour cream, soda, baking powder, flour, allspice, chopped walnuts and dates (cut up with scissors).
Drop by spoonful on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: christmas relish
directions: Cut tops off peppers; leave seeds in.
Cut or chop in small pieces.
Pour boiling water over the peppers and let stand about 10 minutes.
Chop onions and celery and pour boiling water over them and let stand about 10 minutes.
Drain both of the mixtures and put into the remaining ingredients.
Let cook for 20 minutes and seal.

title: black walnut filling
directions: Combine brown sugar, white sugar and milk.
Boil until it becomes like syrup.
Add egg and flour or cornstarch; boil a few minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add walnuts and beat.
Cool filling.
Spread between yellow or white cake layers and on top.

title: f.b.c.  party punch
directions: Make syrup of water and sugar (just bring to a hard boil). While hot, add jello and dissolve well.
Cool slightly and add lemonade and orange juice, stirring until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and extract.
Put in containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, put in punch bowl and add clear carbonated drink. The base can be refrozen.

title: grandma's butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into a long roll about 3 inches thick and wrap in wax paper.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Slice and bake approximately at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Can keep in freezer as long as you wish, up to 3 months.
Bake when ready.)

title: chicken delicious
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Mix cream of chicken soup with can of water.
Sprinkle rice in bottom of 3-quart casserole and add chicken.
Pour mushrooms over chicken, cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken fajitas(4 servings)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add green and red pepper, onion, and garlic; cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove vegetables, set aside.
Add chicken and oregano to skillet and cook 4 minutes.
Return vegetables to pan.
Add wine, season with salt and pepper.
Cover 2 minutes.
Warm tortillas and fill with chicken mixture.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan, add bread crumbs and stir. Layer into 2 qt. casserole, 1/3 of bread crumbs, 1/2 asparagus, 2 sliced eggs, 1/2 pimentos, and 1 can of mushroom soup. Repeat layers and top with remaining 1/3 bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jiffy chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a bowl with a spoon until well blended.
Fold in vinegar fast.
Pour in a greased and floured pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan or 30 to 35 minutes in 8-inch round pan.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat; bring to a boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. (Start timing when mixture starts to "bubble" around edge of pan.) Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute (until marshmallows melt and blend).
Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: cheese burger bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Put in bottom of wide casserole dish.
Pour soup over; place cheese on top.
Cover the cheese with the biscuits.
Bake in 400° oven.
Take out when biscuits are done.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Knead with hands until mixed good.
Make into a ball.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Cut apples crosswise into 9 slices.
In a saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, combine melted margarine, corn syrup, brown sugar and cinnamon. Arrange apple slices in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: heavenly heavenly
directions: Whip up cream and set aside.
Beat butter; add eggs and powdered sugar.
Put in pie shells.
Add strawberries with juice on top of butter mixture.
Put whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin; mix well and add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir until all is moistened.
Spoon into 2 (8 x 3-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (or until toothpick inserted comes out clean).

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Place in crock-pot in order given.
Do not stir.
Cover.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours, on high for 4 to 6 hours.
Do not lift lid or stir during cooking.
Serves 12.

title: rich scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Work in flour.
Press into molds or baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes until light golden brown.

title: fresh blackberry cobbler
directions: Cook berries covered with
water
and 1/2 cup sugar for 15 minutes.
Set aside.

title: company sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet until browned; add onion and cook with sausage until clear, stirring well and drain.
In large bowl, combine all other ingredients; add sausage and onion, mix well.
Pour into a sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; stir and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
If desired, garnish with mushrooms and bell pepper strips.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: western pot roast
directions: In heavy pot, brown on all sides of boneless ground or chunk roast in oil.
Add chopped onion and cook until golden.
Combine catsup, vinegar, Lea & Perrins sauce, brown sugar, cider and salt. Pour over meat.
Simmer, covered, until meat is tender for about 3 hours.
Serve sliced with sauce, along with onions, carrots and potatoes, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: jello chocolate cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Let stand to cool.
Combine cake mix, baking powder, salad oil and eggs and beat.
Add Jell-O and continue beating (total beating time about 4 minutes).
Bake at 350°.
For 9 x 13-inch pan, bake for 35 minutes.
For cupcakes, bake 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and top with Ritz crackers or bread crumbs, crushed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gray lumber company's favorite cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake until done.

title: swedish coconut cookies
directions: Roll into balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: dropped penuche
directions: Boil until soft ball forms, 240°.
Let sit until cool.
Beat until creamy.
Drop on wax paper.
Put 1/2 nuts on top of each piece.

title: creamy lemon lime jello
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and marshmallows.
Mix together and add 3 cups boiling water and large lemon Jell-O.
Mix together until creamy.
Let stand.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: easy roast beef
directions: Place roast (frozen okay) in 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.
Use salt, pepper and seasoned salt as desired.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Pour mushroom sauce over top of roast and in pan.
Rinse can with water and pour in bottom of pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake 6 to 7 hours at 325° if frozen, less if not frozen (test for doneness after 4 hours).
Use juice for gravy.

title: italian style asparagus
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus and discard.
If possible, cook stalks whole or cut to equal size.
Layer in pan and pour boiling water over asparagus.
Cover pan and cook for no more than 3 minutes.
Asparagus should be crisp-tender.
Drain well.
While still hot, pour over the Italian salad dressing and let marinate while cooling.
Can be served hot, but is very good cold.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: *Or 5 cups white flour.

title: doyle's beef stew
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch cubes.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Bring 1/4 cup water to a boil in a large pot.
Coat meat with flour mix.
Put in water and cook on each side until develops a gray look.
The meat browns slightly.
Add Worcestershire sauce, 1 1/2 cups water and tomatoes.
Cover pot. When steaming point is reached, turn heat to low and cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut celery, onions, carrots and pepper into pieces.
Add with potatoes to pot. Cook until everything is tender, about 1 hour.

title: white icing
directions: Put cup of sugar in a saucepan; add water and cook over low heat until fluffy.
Add three marshmallows, then spread on cake all fixed with the filling.

title: cream puff paste
directions: Put butter, milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
When boiling, add the flour and stir up briskly until the paste is smooth.

(If the paste is removed from the fire too soon, the puffs may not spring properly during the baking process.) After taking from the fire, mix in one egg at a time and work well each time before adding another egg.
When all the eggs are added, drop on a baking sheet, the size of an egg yolk for puffs, or in finger shapes for eclairs and bake in an oven at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring, vinegar and cocoa together; set aside. Cream Wesson oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add color mixture. Add soda and salt to flour.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk, alternating.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 4 layer cake pans at 350° for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(Can freeze until ready to use.)

title: vegetable stir fry
directions: Heat 2 Tbsp. oil cut up vegetables.
Mix seasoning mix with 1/4 c. water till smooth.
Add all to oil and cook at medium high. Stir constantly till tender.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Place drained crabmeat, chopped onion and cheese on bottom of one pie crust.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add half and half with salt and pepper.
Beat until all well mixed.
Pour into pie crust.

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Place pot roast into crock-pot. Add water, salt and pepper. Peel and cut up potatoes and place in crock-pot. Let cook on high for 5 to 6 hours. When pot roast is ready, put about 4 tablespoons oil in skillet and let it heat. When it is hot, put 2 or 3 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper. Stir continuously until brown. Pour into crock-pot over roast and potatoes. Stir. This makes the gravy. Serve with corn bread or hot biscuits.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Place in a baking pan (shallow).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Leftovers make superb sandwiches.

title: chicken capri parmigiana
directions: Blend the Ricotta with salt, pepper and oregano.
Rub chicken with garlic powder and brown in skillet with 4 tablespoons of oil, approximately 12 minutes each side.
Remove and cool.
Place chicken in baking dish side by side.
Spoon 1/4 cup seasoned Ricotta and 1/4 cup crushed tomatoes in center of each breast. Top each breast with 2 slices Mozzarella and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: texas tumbleweeds
directions: Combine almond bark and peanut butter chips in a 2-quart microwave dish.
Microwave at 50% power for 4 minutes or until melted.
Stir in peanuts and potato sticks.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax-lined cookie sheets.
Chill until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, chicken soup and broth.
Layer soup, chicken and stuffing mix (mixed with oleo).
Put in large baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Sift the dry ingredients and add the egg-milk mixture.
Heat a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with the 4 tablespoons oil.
Coat the pan well with the oil.
Pour off remaining oil into the bread mixture and beat well.
Fill the oiled pan and bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, mushrooms and water chestnuts; pour into bottom of casserole dish.

title: grandma walsh's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into Teflon coated or buttered and floured pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mud hens
directions: Cream butter and granulated sugar.
Add 3 egg yolks and 1 egg white.
Blend.
Add flour and vanilla.
Grease and flour pan. Roll out dough.
Cream brown sugar and 2 egg whites; spread on dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar.
Pour over previous mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Mix all together and chill.
May need to add a few drops of green food coloring.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: swiss steak
