directions: Cut 1 1/2 pounds tenderized round steak into small pieces. Season and flour. Brown a small amount of water. When all are browned, cover steak with water and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. While steak is simmering, grate 1 1/2 cups Velveeta or American cheese. Stir cheese into steak and gravy. Simmer about 15 minutes more. Serve over rice or with mashed potatoes.

title: mary's famous ham biscuits
directions: Melt butter and saute onion. Add poppy seeds, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Spread on both sides of rolls. Add ham and cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Ham biscuits can be microwaved, if desired.

title: pollo bueno
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stew chicken; bone it and set aside. Skim fat from chicken broth and use broth to make chili.
Brown flour in skillet.
Add chili powder and stir in broth; simmer, stirring, for 10 minutes, until thicken.
Place corn tortillas, one at a time, in boiling water for 5 to 10 seconds to soften. Layer corn tortillas, chicken, rice, onion and cheese.
Cover with chili; garnish with additional cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and let simmer all day.
Add salt and pepper.

title: warm bacon dressing
directions: Fry 6 slices cut up bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towel. Add 1 cup water to bacon grease and bring to boil.
Make paste of flour, salt, sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 well beaten egg to paste mixture.
Remove water mixture from heat and stir in egg mixture slowly.
Return to heat and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/4 cup vinegar.
Add bacon pieces right before you serve over lettuce or endive.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan and add garlic and parsley; cook over medium heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add clam juice, clams, salt and pepper and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add butter.
Stir until butter is melted. Serve at once over hot, cooked pasta.
Especially delicious when served with garlic bread!

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with crackers, Hawaiian bread, etc.

title: date pudding
directions: Dissolve brown sugar, water and butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine white sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, dates, milk and vanilla.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pea soup deluxe
directions: Soak peas overnight (can soak peas with ham).
Simmer on low heat until peas are soft (usually 3 hours on low).
Stir often and use a heavy pan as this will scorch easily if not careful.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Chock-full of fresh vegetables, this main dish is as easy to prepare as it is delicious.
Serve over chow mein noodles for added crunch.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In second bowl, blend eggs, oil, milk and lemon juice.
Mix liquid mixture into flour mixture until flour disappears.
Fold in blueberries and place in paper cupcake holders.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 18.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and pecans.
Heat oven to 375°. Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place about 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: sad cake
directions: Combine sugar and Bisquick until free of lumps.
Make hole in center of dry mixture.
Pour in oil, eggs and pecans.
Stir until mixed well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes (no longer) at 350°.
Add 1 cup coconut, if desired.

title: neiman's cookies recipe
directions: Blend oatmeal until it's fine powder.
Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda together and add to first mixture.
Then add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 5 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.
Recipe may be halved.

title: beef cheese taco dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add Manwich and taco mix.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Melt cheese in a bowl.
Put meat in a round clump and drop on melted cheese so there is a band of cheese around meat.
Serve with taco chips.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fry as you would a pancake.

title: sassy onion dip
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover; chill.
Stir before serving.
Serve with fresh vegetables or Kruncher's potato chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes; sieve.
Make a white sauce of butter, flour and milk. Slowly add hot tomato mixture, stirring constantly.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: While cooking zucchini in a small amount of water, brown hamburger with the onion.
Mix everything together, except the cheese.

title: imitation crab legs and tofu(deep fried)
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients and mix well.
Heat oil in pan and drop ingredients by 1 teaspoon.
Fry until light brown.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Place broccoli in casserole and top with chicken slices.
Combine undiluted chicken soup with mayonnaise, milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May freeze before baking.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Combine peppers in blender and puree.
Add 1 cup vinegar and blend.
Transfer to large deep pan and add remaining vinegar, sugar and cayenne, blending well.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring often.
Add pectin and boil 1 minute longer stirring constantly.
Skim off foam and pour in jars and seal.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour pans.
Beat dry cake mix, water, margarine and eggs on low speed.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of the crushed cookies. Fold remaining crushed cookies into the batter.
Pour into pan. Bake 30 to 37 minutes.
Cool cake completely.
Crush remaining cookies fine.
Mix into frosting.
Layer cake.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Halve, then remove skin and bone from 4 whole chicken breasts (12 oz. each). Pound between pieces of waxed paper until each is about 1/4 inch thick.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze water out of thawed spinach.
(Do not cook.)
Mix with other ingredients and chill.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine crumbs, pecans, sugar and cocoa.
Blend bourbon and syrup.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: open-faced tacos
directions: Brown beef; add Ro-Tel tomatoes, beans and soup and simmer at least 45 minutes.
Crush Fritos Lights for each plate.
Ladle sauce over Fritos, then add cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions and sour cream.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: fred's linguine with shrimp
directions: Cook linguine to package directions and set aside in large serving bowl.
Heat olive oil in 2-quart saucepot and saute garlic and shallots for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Then add tomatoes, parsley, wine, red pepper flakes, oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Then add shrimp; cook another 5 minutes.
Pour shrimp sauce over linguine and serve.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove 12 large leaves from cabbage.
Trim off thick part of each leaf.
Let boiling water stand on leaves a few minutes, so they become easy to roll.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 3 small or 2 large greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes real well too!

title: chicken primavera
directions: In skillet, blend first 3 ingredients.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling and reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
This is quick and very good.

title: lime pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and peel large ones.
Cut in 1/4-inch pieces. Slice and soak 24 hours in lime water.
Remove and soak in clear water 2 hours.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Dry all vegetables between paper towels (about 1 hour).
Layer in order of recipe (using oblong dish, sheet cake size).
Blend mayonnaise and sugar, spread over salad as icing.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix well potatoes, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour.
Mix in shortening and potatoes.
Gradually stir in milk (try to handle dough as little as possible).
Roll onto a floured surface.
Cut into biscuits.
Makes about 25 biscuits.
Bake in 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 25.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together in large punch bowl and enjoy.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta in water until tender; drain.
Add tomatoes, cucumber, onion, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour salad dressing and seasoning over pasta mixture until well covered.
Toss well. Best if allowed to marinate in refrigerator 4 hours before serving.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Just dump all ingredients into bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into floured Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: jello finger jigglers
directions: Boil 4 cups water.
Immediately stir in Knox and gelatin. Chill about 3 hours until completely set.
Cut into squares or use a cookie cutter to cut into shapes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Peel and core 6 to 8 medium apples. Cut in 1/2-inch slices to make 4 cups.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
In a large pot cook about 3 to 4 hours.
Keep water well over top of beans.

title: bundt coffee cake
directions: Place frozen rolls randomly in Bundt pan.
Mix pudding mix, brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Melt oleo and drizzle over rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
Let set overnight or 8 to 10 hours to allow rolls to rise.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion and drain.
Add tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and spaghetti.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix Mozzarella cheese and sour cream and spread over meat mixture.
Place rolls spread out on top.
Melt margarine and spread on rolls.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° until rolls are golden brown.

title: black beans
directions: Wash and discard any unwanted beans.
Soak beans in water overnight.
Using medium heat, cook the beans in the same water until the beans are tender.
Saute the onion and garlic in oil and add the chili peppers and oregano.
Cook
3 minutes over medium heat.
Add this mixture to the beans.
Leave enough water remaining for the sauce.
(You may need to add more.)
At this time add the salt, vinegar, sugar and bay leaves.
Cover the pot, leaving an escape for the steam.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes or until the sauce thickens to your taste.

title: mexican hot potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef with onion and garlic; drain. Stir in sour cream, salsa, oregano, chili powder and salt.
Serve over hot, baked potato and with guacamole on the side.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix together next 4 ingredients.
Then combine the 2 mixtures and bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: special scrambled eggs
directions: Drop small spoonfuls of cream cheese into scrambled egg mixture and whip.
Cook in the usual fashion.
This just adds a special touch to your eggs.

title: seafood primavera
directions: Melt butter with minced garlic.
Slowly cook fish in this. Mix the sauce as per packet.
Mix in cooked vegetables.
Blend all these and serve over cooked linguine noodles.

title: fred's favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, crackers, egg, onion and seasonings.
Mix well. Make a hole in the mixture and fill with about 1/4 cup undiluted tomato soup.
Mix again, working in the tomato soup.
Form mixture into loaf and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish coated with vegetable oil.
Dilute remaining soup with 3/4 cup water and pour over the meat loaf.
Surround with potatoes and carrots.
Salt and pepper vegetables to taste.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove foil and bake until meat loaf is brown on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Let frozen spinach thaw, squeezing out all the water.
Mix all other ingredients and add spinach.
Let set for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook and tear apart chicken.
Cook rice as directed.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peasant spaghetti
directions: Crush garlic clove with salt.
Scald tomatoes, peel and cut into
sections.
Wash and chop basil. Add water, olive oil and dash of pepper.
Let set about an hour for flavors to mix. Cook spaghetti al dente.
Drain and add tomato mixture.
Serve in soup bowl. Serves 4.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add condensed milk and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: turkey fry
directions: Heat hog lard until hot enough to cook potatoes.
Combine all ingredients and inject into turkey.
Ready to cook.
For every pound, cook 5 minutes.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit.
Combine all fruit in a bowl.
Combine pudding mix, milk and orange juice concentrate in mixer bowl. Beat at high speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add sour cream; beat well. Pour over fruit mixture.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator. Yields 10 servings.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, white sugar and 2 eggs.
Beat until nice and creamy.
Add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Take dry ingredients (flour, salt and baking soda), mix in your liquid mixture.
Last, add walnuts.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Preheat oven at least 15 minutes at 375°.
Beat egg whites until very stiff with salt and cream of tartar.
Add sugar gradually, beating continually.
Beat until glossy.
Add chips and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls (small) on ungreased cookie sheet. Put in oven and immediately turn oven off.
Leave in oven at least 5 hours or overnight.
Do not open oven until time is up!!

title: oven baked crab dip
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Gently stir in crab meat.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken until done and remove from bone; save broth. Boil spaghetti in chicken broth until tender.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break apart broccoli and cauliflower.
Add green onions.
Mix remaining ingredients (except cherry tomatoes) and pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight.
Top with cherry tomatoes.

title: sticky pecan rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Sprinkle pudding and nuts on top.
Combine brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon in pan and bring to a boil, stirring.
Pour over rolls. Let raise overnight.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let rest a minute before flip over on dish.

title: creole macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add macaroni, onion, pepper, oregano and dry mustard.
Cook on medium heat for 7 to 10 minutes.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until macaroni is tender and water boiled out.
Stir in evaporated milk, pimento and cheese.
Cook about 5 minutes on low until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll in balls.
Brown in hot skillet, then mix package of sauce in Rice-A-Roni with 2 cups hot water.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken marco polo
directions: Bake chicken in oven for 1 hour.
Split chicken apart and debone.
Cook spinach and drain.
Line a buttered casserole with the spinach.
Place chicken breasts on top of spinach.
Use an 8 x 12 x 2-inch dish.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on the box.
Mix cream cheese and milk together, add pudding.
Put in refrigerator until mixture sets up. Put this mixture on top of cooled cake.
Then add a layer of pineapple, a layer of Cool Whip and top with coconut.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine rice, 1/2 gallon milk and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until the milk is absorbed by the rice (about 1 hour).

title: banana butterscotch muffinsceres, california
directions: Puree banana in blender.
In medium bowl, combine pureed banana, egg, sugar, milk, oil and vanilla.

title: mexican crinkles
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in syrup and chocolate.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon into creamed mixture.
Shape dough into balls the size of walnuts and roll in sugar.
Place balls on ungreased baking sheet, 3 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stuffing and melted butter.
Put in casserole.
Put stuffing mix over top, spreading evenly.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir every 7 to 10 minutes.
Add peanuts last 10 minutes.

title: mock cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries with sugar.
Let set overnight.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: french's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shake well before using.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Slice onions.
Add to sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Add beans and crumble bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Can also be served cold.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick. Add remaining 3 ingredients and mix in mixer until smooth.

title: purple cow
directions: Take the frozen grape juice stuff.
Make it.
Take some time to roll it around in your mouth!
Then fill your mug with 3 scoops of ice cream.
Pour grape juice until full.
Stir.
Chug-a-lug.
Share it with your buddies.
Not recommended use in great quantitys. Although it is very good too much really hurts your stomach.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, onion, celery and almonds. Blend mayonnaise, mustard and cream. Fold into chicken mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours. Add shoestring potatoes and carrots just before serving. Toss well.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Use high
speed
mixer	to
mix
butter, shortening and vanilla until creamy. Add sugar and mix until smooth.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook to
hard
boil,
Take
off
heat
and add 1 teaspoon baking
soda.
Stir quickly and pour over 1 (6 ounce) bag of
popped
corn
(3/4 cup unpopped) in large mixing bowl. Mix and spread on 2 jelly roll or cookie type sheets.
Bake at 200° for 30 minutes on
each
side,
mixing
at
turns to coat evenly.
Pour out on waxed
paper
and separate while hot into small pieces.

title: congealed salad
directions: Bring can of pineapple to a boil. Add jello.
Dissolve and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Congeal.

title: sis. dorothy wells' chocolate pudding or pie filling
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar with a fork.
Add 3 tablespoons of flour; mix well.
Add vanilla, milk and dash of salt.
Add 1/2 stick of margarine with all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Heat on medium heat until thick.

title: jellied cranberry cheese salad
directions: Dissolve candies in the boiling water; add lemon gelatin and lemon juice.
Stir to dissolve gelatin and cool to room temperature.
Add cranberry sauce (if jellied cranberry sauce is used, beat with a rotary beater).
Pour 1/2 of the cranberry gelatin mixture into a 9-inch square pan.
Set aside remaining cranberry gelatin mixture at room temperature; cover.
Chill mixture in the pan until firm, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: hasty fruit cobbler
directions: Add sugar to Master Mix.
Beat egg and add to dry mixture with milk.
Heat fruit and liquid to boiling.
Sweeten if necessary. Grease casserole dish or deep pan with butter.
Pour batter in baking dish, then add hot fruit.
Bake immediately in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter.
Beat egg in measuring cup; add enough milk to make 2/3 c. Mix flour mixture and egg mixture.
Turn out onto lightly floured pastry sheet.
Knead just until smooth. Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thick and cut with doughnut cutter. Deep fry for 3-4 minutes at 450°.
Drain on paper towels.
Sift confectioners sugar over doughnuts.
Makes about 15 doughnuts.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Crumble and brown
sausage.
Drain. Add onions and cook until transparent. Add
spaghetti
sauce,
mushrooms
(I	use canned mushrooms at times) and olives.
Heat and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Evenly
arrange
Mozzarella
cheese over this mixture (slices or	shredded).
Whirl or beat eggs, milk, flour, oil and
salt
until
smooth.
Pour
over
Mozzarella. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Dip chicken in beaten egg; roll in flour.
Fry until golden. Combine remaining ingredients.
Place chicken in single layer in baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Turn chicken 4 times while baking to keep sauce covering them.

title: sweet bread french toast
directions: Bread eggs into pie or cake pan and beat with fork.
Add salt and milk and mix together with the eggs using fork.
Heat about 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Dip bread in egg mixture and cook in the skillet.
Turn over and brown bottom.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with butter and syrup or jelly.

title: dark cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl combine sugar and cornstarch. Stir in cherries, juice and food coloring.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Combine dry cake mix and melted butter or margarine. (Mixture will be crumbly.) Sprinkle over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.
tags: Duncan Hines cherry supreme deluxe cake mix

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Add Worcestershire and celery salt.
Stir until smooth.
Add oysters and liquid.
Cook over low heat until edges curl.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly over low heat.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle with paprika. Frozen oysters may be used.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill for several hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Line cake pans (13 x 9-inch) with graham cracker crust.
Cook vanilla pudding as directed and pour over crust.
Layer drained pineapple, sliced bananas (cut lengthwise) enough to cover cherry or strawberry pie filling.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Leave cake set overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, both soups, 1 can of milk, meat and onion powder in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour evenly over mixture.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: speedy mediterranean shrimp
directions: In a 10-inch skilled over medium high heat, bring zucchini, tomatoes and wine to boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 4 minutes stirring occasionally until zucchini is tender but still crisp.
Add shrimp and olives to zucchini mixture and simmer partially covered for 3 to 4 minutes until shrimp are just opaque and cooked through, uncovering several times to stir.
Remove from heat and stir in pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi spoon bread
directions: Place cornmeal in a saucepan.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 3 tablespoons butter and salt, stirring until butter is melted.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve immediately with butter.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat Crisco and milk together; add yeast.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Let rise.
Roll out on floured surface. Cut out.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: hungarian crepes
directions: Combine ingredients; beat with mixer until well mixed.
Heat a lightly greased 6-inch skillet.
Pour in 2 to 3 tablespoons batter.
Lift and tilt skillet to spread batter.
Brown on 1 side only (do not turn).
Invert on paper towel; remove crepe.
Makes 16 to 18 crepes.

title: cherry tart
directions: Mix Dream Whip topping according to package directions.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, Dream Whip and nuts. Pour into crusts.
Chill.
Top mixture with pie filling.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded measuring tablespoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies.
Will appear light and moist.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine enchilada and tomato sauces.
Brown meat and add salt and pepper; drain.
Dip tortillas in sauces and place in layers in a casserole dish.
Place a layer of meat, a layer of cheese and a layer of onions.
Start with tortillas. Repeat until everything is gone.
Pour any remaining sauce over top.
Cover with foil and bake about 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix and pour over fruit when ready to serve. Good with chunk pineapple.

title: asparagus guacamole dip
directions: Cook the asparagus spears.
Blend all the ingredients in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Chill and serve.
Try it; you won't believe it's so good!
Serves 8.
Contains 0 g fat and 54 calories.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine and sift dry ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add walnuts.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: walnut infused acini de pepe pasta(with prosciutto, red peppers and artichoke hearts)
directions: Saute walnuts and shallots with olive oil; add wine and reduce until dry.
Add cream; reduce by 1/3.
Season with salt and pepper. Toss with pasta and Parmesan.
Garnish with remaining ingredients. Serves 4.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain.
In 10-inch skillet, cook vegetables in 2 tablespoons of margarine for 4 to 5 minutes.
Melt remaining margarine in 3-quart pan over low heat.
Stir in whipping cream, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly. Add pasta, vegetables and Parmesan cheese.
Stir until thoroughly heated.

title: zucchini-seafood casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch). Mix all ingredients.
Spread in dish.
Bake, uncovered, until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with zucchini slices, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 1-inch chunks.
Cook, covered, in boiling water for about 20 minutes, or until tender.
Drain.
While cooking carrots, mix all other ingredients, except butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute. Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots.
Stir and serve.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Prepare oven to 275°.
Saute roast, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake about 5 to 6 hours.
Shred with fork.
Serve on buns.
Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: cheddar vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 3/4 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes longer.

title: spread or dip
directions: Mix together and serve on party rye bread.

title: baked (or fried) apple pies
directions: Cook apples until done or tender.
Mash with a potato masher, add sugar and mix well.
Continue to cook until no longer soupy, stirring often.
Make a nice rich pastry by mixing flour, Crisco and milk.
Roll out dough into balls half the size of a biscuit. On a floured piece of wax paper, roll each ball into a thin circle.
Dip a teaspoon into water and moisten edges of circle to make them stick together.
Place a heaping tablespoon of fruit on one half of the circle of dough.
Fold the other half of circle over the fruit and seal with a fork dipped in flour.
Place the pie on a well-greased bread pan.
Cook in a 400° oven until brown on bottom.
Brush a teaspoon of corn oil on each pie and turn over and brown on the other side.
When done, brush the tops with melted margarine or corn oil.

title: cream cheese jello salad
directions: Make a paste of jello and cream cheese.
Add 1 cup boiling water, pineapple, salt, vinegar and nuts.
Chill.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Mix the Parmesan cheese and egg and divide in half.

Divide all ingredients in half. Divide bread in half and roll out. Spread egg mixture, pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with oregano leaves. Roll in jelly roll fashion into two loaves. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate mint truffles
directions: Melt chocolate chips with milk until smooth (about 3 minutes in microwave).
Chill 2 hours until firm.

title: bangers and mash
directions: Pierce sausages in a couple of places with fork. Fry in skillet or bake in pan (350° for about 30 to 45 minutes) until done.
Fry onion in pan in which the sausages were cooked or cook in microwave without fat.
Make gravy mix.
Stir onions, salt and pepper into gravy. Serve gravy on mashed potatoes with sausages alongside.
Makes 4 servings.

title: world's best pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Sift flour with soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
Add dry ingredients to other mixture alternating with water.
Place in 3 small loaf pans or 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Freezes well.

title: pudding pie dessert
directions: Freeze candy bar before starting.
Mix flour, butter and pecans, then press in bottom of glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into crust.
Chill.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in heavy pan.
Put the peanuts in a 275° oven while cooking the other ingredients.
Bring the sugar mixture to a boil (280°).
Add salted peanuts and boil to 305°.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon of baking soda; mix in well. Pour on greased cookie
sheet (10 x 13-inch).
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before removing.
Wipe brittle off with paper towel. Turn and blot until cool.
Break into pieces.

title: rice krispies chicken(amish recipe)
directions: Roll chicken pieces in melted margarine, then into Rice Krispies mixture.
Arrange on shallow pan.
Bake at 275° for several hours.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients and shake until coated.
Put into shallow pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally for 40 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: jean fuller's baked pineapple
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add to remaining ingredients, except butter.
Put into a greased casserole.
Dot pineapple mixture with the butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Combine buttermilk with baking soda, water and molasses. Allow to rest for 5 minutes until bubbly.
Blend whole wheat flour, oat bran flour (oatmeal can be used), white flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Mix just to blend.
Gently add pecans; do not overbeat.
Pour into 12 lined muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Muffins will be dark and firm to touch.
Serve warm.

title: quick oven baked beans
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well, tossing lightly. Place into well-greased shallow dish. Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: taco pie
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush Doritos and sprinkle half over crust.
Set other half aside.
Brown meat, drain and add taco seasoning with 1/2 cup water and sauce or salsa; pour beef mixture over Doritos.
Spread sour cream over beef.
Add remaining Doritos.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.
Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and morsels.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Mix in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Serve hot.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except caraway seed and chives.
Top with caraway seed and chives.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: swiss-onion-zucchini bake
directions: Peel and thinly slice onion.
Separate into rings.
Saute onion and zucchini in butter until tender.
Place in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper, mustard and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candied pecans
directions: Bring sour cream and sugars to a boil.
Add vanilla and pecans
and dry on waxed paper.

title: southern cornbread thanksgiving stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine crumbled cornbread, dried white bread slices and saltines; mix together and set aside.
In a large skillet, saut the chopped celery and onion in butter until transparent, approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour sauted mixture over cornbread mixture.
Add the stock.
Mix well; taste and add salt, pepper to taste, sage and poultry seasoning. Mix well.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Reserve 2 heaping tablespoons of this mixture for the giblet gravy.
Pour mixture into a greased pan and bake until dressing is done, about 45 minutes.
Serve with turkey as a side dish.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soda, in a 4-quart saucepan. Place on medium heat.
Bring to a boil and cook 15 to 20 minutes (or until it turns caramel colored), stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Add soda, mixing well.
Pour onto 2 buttered cookie sheets.
When cool, break into desired size pieces.

title: whip cream icing
directions: Add milk and flour in saucepan and bring to boil or until thickened.
Remove from burner and let cool.
Combine Crisco and oleo in bowl.
Cream well.
Add powdered sugar and beat on high until creamy.
Add milk mixture to sugar mixture.
Beat at high speed until fluffy and creamy.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup Bundt pan or 10 inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, combine sugar and margarine; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Gradually add 2 cups powdered sugar, blend well by hand.
Stir in flour and remaining cake ingredients until well blended. Do not omit nuts.
They are essential for the success of the recipe.
Spoon batter into greased and floured pan; spread evenly.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease a 9 to 10-cup fluted tube pan; dust with sugar. Mix chocolate chips, walnuts and 2 tablespoons of flour in medium bowl.
Sift remaining flour with baking soda, baking powder and salt.
With electric mixer, cream butter until light.
Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Fold chocolate/walnut mixture into batter.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake about 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Invert onto rack.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Add strawberry jello to first mixture while it is still hot (add a little red food color).
The cooler you let this get, the firmer your pie.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil water.
Add sugar, stirring until it dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Arrange in casserole dish as follows:
layer of beans, layer of potato chips, layer of soup, layer of cheese, layer of eggs, layer of onions.
Repeat.
Bake in 350° about 30 minutes. Asparagus may also be used.

title: fruit and champagne punch
directions: Blend strawberries, frozen lemonade and crushed pineapple in blender.
Pour into punch bowl.
Pour in champagne, ginger ale and club soda.
Add ice cubes or ice ring.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, lemon slices or maraschino cherries.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl, except for shells, spaghetti sauce and 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese.
Mix well.
Pour half can of spaghetti sauce to bottom of large baking pan.
Spoon by large tablespoon combined ingredients into each shell and place in pan.
Cover shells with remaining sauce and top with the rest of the Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.
Enjoy!
